{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran", "text_new": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Iran}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran\n| map1 = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Iran (Density).svg\n| legend1 =\n{{legend|#f2a88d|Confirmed cases 10\u201399}}\n{{legend|#e36654|Confirmed cases 100\u2013499}}\n{{legend|#e42a4b|Confirmed cases 500\u2013999}}\n{{legend|#87353f|Confirmed cases 1000\u20139999}}\n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Iran]]\n| first_case = [[Qom]]\n| arrival_date = 19 February 2020 <br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month=02|day=19|year=2020}} ago)\n| origin = [[Wuhan]], [[China]] (initial reports)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/our-columnists/how-iran-became-a-new-epicenter-of-the-coronavirus-outbreak|title=How Iran Became a New Epicenter of the Coronavirus Outbreak|first=Robin|last=Wright|website=The New Yorker|access-date=7 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303213444/https://www.newyorker.com/news/our-columnists/how-iran-became-a-new-epicenter-of-the-coronavirus-outbreak|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| confirmed_cases = 44,605<ref name=\"coronatracker\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.coronatracker.com/country/ir|title=COVID-19 Iran Corona Tracker|website=Corona Tracker}}</ref>\n| deaths = 2,898<ref name=\"coronatracker\"/>\n| recovery_cases = 14,656<ref name=\"coronatracker\"/>\n| suspected_cases =\n| total_ili = \n| website = {{URL|http://behdasht.gov.ir/}}\n}}\n\nDuring the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]], [[:Iran]] reported its first confirmed cases of [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]] infections on 19 February 2020 in [[Qom]].<ref name=\"NYT_Iran_19Feb_first2\" /> {{As of|2020|03|31}}, according to the Iranian Ministry of Health, there had been 2,898 [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] deaths in Iran with 44,605 confirmed infections.<ref name=\"coronatracker\"/> As of 31 March 2020, Iran has the sixth-highest number of COVID-19 deaths after [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|Italy]], [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in mainland China|China]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain|Spain]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|United States]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in France|France]], and the sixth-highest number of SARS-CoV-2 cases in the world.\n\nThe virus may have been brought to the country by a merchant from [[Qom]] who had travelled to China.<ref name=\"newyorker1\"/> Iran became a centre of the spread of the virus in the Middle East,<ref name=\"nyt\"/><ref name=newyorker1 /> with more than ten countries tracing their cases back to Iran by 28 February.<ref name=\"newyorker1\"/> Government's actions include cancellation of public events and [[Friday prayers]], closure of schools, universities, shopping centres and bazaars as well as holy shrines, and banning of festival celebrations.<ref name=\"aljeera17012020\">{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-pandemic-kill-millions-iran-200317135500255.html |title=Coronavirus pandemic 'could kill millions' in Iran |date=17 March 2020 |work=Al Jazeera |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317222216/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-pandemic-kill-millions-iran-200317135500255.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"bbc24032020\" /> Economic measures were also announced to help families and businesses. The government has rejected plans to quarantine entire cities and areas, and heavy traffic between cities continued ahead of [[Nowruz]] despite the government's intention to limit travel. The government later announced a ban on travel between cities following an increase in number of new cases.<ref name=quarantine /><ref name=\"bbc24032020\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51642926 |title=Coronavirus: Iran is facing a major challenge controlling the outbreak |work=BBC |date=24 March 2020 |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304101128/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51642926 |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nSome non-Iranian-government sources estimates of the numbers of COVID-19 deaths are much higher than official values.<ref name=\"AJE_Qom_coverup_50deaths\" /><ref name=\"BBC_210_deaths_Iran\" /><ref name=\"france24\"/> The Iranian government has also been accused of cover-ups, censorship and mismanagement.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/brian-hook-says-iran-lied-to-own-people-over-coronavirus/30470777.html |title=Brian Hook Says Iran 'Lied To Own People' Over Coronavirus |website=Radio Farda |access-date=11 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313124419/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/brian-hook-says-iran-lied-to-own-people-over-coronavirus/30470777.html |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-envoy-says-iran-lied-to-own-people-over-coronavirus/articleshow/74498219.cms|title=US envoy says Iran 'lied to own people' over coronavirus|website=Times of India|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305212012/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-envoy-says-iran-lied-to-own-people-over-coronavirus/articleshow/74498219.cms|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jpost.com/Middle-East/Irans-government-and-media-lied-about-coronavirus-outbreak-riots-erupt-618431|title=Iran's government and media lied about coronavirus outbreak|website=Jerusalem Post|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301013021/https://www.jpost.com/Middle-East/Irans-government-and-media-lied-about-coronavirus-outbreak-riots-erupt-618431|archive-date=1 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"newyorker1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/our-columnists/how-iran-became-a-new-epicenter-of-the-coronavirus-outbreak|title=How Iran Became a New Epicenter of the Coronavirus Outbreak|website=New Yorker|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303213444/https://www.newyorker.com/news/our-columnists/how-iran-became-a-new-epicenter-of-the-coronavirus-outbreak|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> However, the [[World Health Organisation]] says that it has not seen problems with Iran's reported figures,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/02/irans-coronavirus-updates-cannot-entirely-be-trusted-expert-says.html|title=Iran's coronavirus updates cannot 'entirely' be trusted, expert says|website=cnbc|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303042553/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/02/irans-coronavirus-updates-cannot-entirely-be-trusted-expert-says.html|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> although later a WHO official indicated that only a fifth of the cases may be identified in Iran due to testing being limited only to severe cases initially, as was the situation with some European countries.<ref name=\"WHO estimate\"/>\n\nMultiple Iranian government ministers and senior officials have been diagnosed SARS-CoV-2 positive, as well as 23 members of the [[Islamic Consultative Assembly|Iranian Parliament]] (around 8% of all MPs).<ref name=henley>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/03/iran-steps-up-coronavirus-efforts-as-23-mps-said-to-be-infected |title=Coronavirus: Iran steps up efforts as 23 MPs said to be infected |first=Jon |last=Henley |date=3 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304031109/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/03/iran-steps-up-coronavirus-efforts-as-23-mps-said-to-be-infected |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> At least 12 sitting or former Iranian politicians and officials had died from the virus by 17 March 2020.<ref name=\"aljeera17012020\"/> Notable individuals reported to have died from COVID-19 include [[Hadi Khosroshahi]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20200227-irans-ex-ambassador-to-vatican-dies-of-coronavirus/ |title=Iran's ex-ambassador to Vatican dies of coronavirus |date=27 February 2020 |work=Middle East Monitor |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305204519/https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20200227-irans-ex-ambassador-to-vatican-dies-of-coronavirus/ |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Mohammad Mirmohammadi]], [[Hossein Sheikholeslam]], [[Fatemeh Rahbar]], [[Reza Mohammadi Langroudi]],<ref name=\"Langroudi\"/> [[Mohammad-Reza Rahchamani]],<ref name=\"Rahchamani\"/> [[Nasser Shabani]],<ref name=\"shabani-dies\"/> [[Hashem Bathaie Golpayegani]],<ref name=\"golpayegani-dies\"/> and [[Hamid Kahram]].<ref name=\"kahram-dies\"/><ref name=\"Ebtekar\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n{{prose|date=March 2020}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus outbreak data/Iran medical cases chart}}\n\n===February 2020===\n*19 February: 2 people tested positive for [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]] in [[Qom]].<ref name=\"NYT_Iran_19Feb_first2\" /> Later that day, the [[Ministry of Health and Medical Education]](MOHME) stated that both had died.<ref name=\"CNBC_Iran_first2deaths\" />\n*20 February: 3 new cases were reported by the Ministry of Health. Two of them were from the city of Qom and one from [[Arak, Iran|Arak]].<ref name=\"ThomReut_20Feb_3new\" />\n*21 February: 13 new cases were reported. Seven cases are from Qom, 4 from Tehran, and 2 from [[Gilan Province]]. Two more people in Iran died from COVID-19.<ref name=\"ThomReut_Iran13cases_2moredeaths\" />\n*22 February: the Ministry of Health reported 10 more infected cases bringing the total to 29 and two more deaths bringing the total to eight. Eight of the new cases were from the city of Qom and two from Tehran.<ref name=\"ThomReut_10new_2deaths\" /> The following day Iran's Health Minister [[Saeed Namaki]] said that one of those who died was a merchant from Qom who traveled regularly using indirect flights between China and Iran after direct flights were suspended between the two countries, and may have brought the virus from China.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-s-health-minister-says-virus-came-from-china-travel/30449759.html |title=Iran's Health Minister Says Virus Came From China Travel |date=23 February 2020 |work=Radio Farda |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224162650/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-s-health-minister-says-virus-came-from-china-travel/30449759.html |archive-date=24 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*23 February: the confirmed cases count rose to 43 over four cities and the COVID-19 death toll to eight.<ref name=\"ThomReut_polls_SARSCoV2\">{{cite news|last1=Hafezi |first1=Parisa |title=Iran announces low poll turnout, blames coronavirus 'propaganda' |date=23 February 2020 |agency=[[Thomson Reuters]] |url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-election-khamenei/iran-announces-low-poll-turnout-blames-coronavirus-propaganda-idUSKCN20H09Z |accessdate=23 February 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200223194037/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-iran-election-khamenei/iran-announces-low-poll-turnout-blames-coronavirus-propaganda-idUSKCN20H09Z |archivedate= 23 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*24 February: Iran's Deputy Minister of Health, Dr.{{ill|Iraj Harirchi|fa|\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u062c \u062d\u0631\u06cc\u0631\u0686\u06cc}}, said that twelve people had died and up to 61 had been infected with the new coronavirus. Parliamentarian [[Ahmad Amirabadi|Ahmad Amirabadi Farahani]]'s claimed that 50 people had died in [[Qom]] from COVID-19, which Harirchi denied.<ref name=\"AJE_Qom_coverup_50deaths\" /> At the press conference, Harirchi coughed and sweated.<ref name=\"MEE_MOHME_deputy_min_positive\" />\n*25 February: Dr. Iraj Harirchi tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 infection.<ref name=\"MEE_MOHME_deputy_min_positive\">{{cite news |title=Iran's deputy health minister tests positive for coronavirus |date=25 February 2020 |newspaper=[[Middle East Eye]] |url= https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/irans-deputy-health-minister-tests-positive-coronavirus |accessdate=25 February 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200225130856/https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/irans-deputy-health-minister-tests-positive-coronavirus |archivedate= 25 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The Iranian government first told Iranian citizens that the U.S. had \"hyped COVID-19 to suppress turnout\" during its government elections, and that it would \"punish anyone spreading rumors about a serious epidemic.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/irans-coronavirus-problem-lot-worse-it-seems/607663/|title=Iran Has Far More Coronavirus Cases Than It Is Letting On|website=The Atlantic|access-date=9 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309232036/https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/irans-coronavirus-problem-lot-worse-it-seems/607663/|archive-date=9 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/coronavirus-iran-struggles-contain-outbreak-how-why-photos-2020-3?IR=T#supreme-leader-ali-khamenei-has-also-been-pictured-wearing-disposable-gloves-during-a-speech-an-apparent-health-measure-that-he-hadnt-appeared-to-take-before-7|title=From silencing medics to banning 'rumors': Here's why Iran is struggling to contain its coronavirus outbreak|website=Business Insider|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315080511/https://www.businessinsider.com/coronavirus-iran-struggles-contain-outbreak-how-why-photos-2020-3?IR=T#supreme-leader-ali-khamenei-has-also-been-pictured-wearing-disposable-gloves-during-a-speech-an-apparent-health-measure-that-he-hadnt-appeared-to-take-before-7|archive-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nationalreview.com/news/iran-to-sentence-citizens-who-spreads-rumors-about-coronavirus-to-flogging-three-years-in-prison/|title=Iran to Sentence Citizens Who \"Spreads Rumors\" about Coronavirus to Flogging, Three Years in Prison|website=National Review|date=26 February 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310160903/https://www.nationalreview.com/news/iran-to-sentence-citizens-who-spreads-rumors-about-coronavirus-to-flogging-three-years-in-prison/|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A closed parliamentary session including Health Minister [[Saeed Namaki]] and Ahmad Amirabadi Farahani was held. Body temperatures were tested prior to the meeting and three members of parliament, including Amirabadi Farahani, were requested to excuse themselves from the session and self-quarantine. All three attended the session. Amirabadi Farahani later spoke with journalists and gave television interviews wearing a mask and pair of gloves.<ref name=\"AlArabiya_Amirabadi_symptoms\">{{cite news|url= https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/24/Iranian-MP-50-dead-from-coronavirus-in-Qom-Health-Minister-to-blame-ILNA.html |title=About 50 dead from coronavirus in Qom, Health Minister to blame: Iran MP on ILNA |date= 25 February 2020 |newspaper=[[Al Arabiya]] |accessdate=25 February 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200225132649/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/24/Iranian-MP-50-dead-from-coronavirus-in-Qom-Health-Minister-to-blame-ILNA.html |archivedate= 25 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> Mahmoud Sadeghi, an MP from Tehran, also tested positive for the virus.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51628484 |title=Top Iran health official gets virus as fears grow |date=25 February 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=27 February 2020 |language=en-GB |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303072933/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51628484 |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Ebtekar\">{{cite web |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/27/Iranian-Vice-President-Masoumeh-Ebtekar-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-Report.html |title=Iranian Vice President Masoumeh Ebtekar tests positive for coronavirus: Report |website=english.alarabiya.net |date=26 February 2020 |language=en |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227135129/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/27/Iranian-Vice-President-Masoumeh-Ebtekar-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-Report.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*26 February: The Ministry of Health reported 44 more new confirmed cases and 4 new deaths.<ref name=\"MOH26Feb\">{{cite web| title=Iran Coronavirus Cases| website=Worldometer| url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/country/iran/| access-date=23 March 2020| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309183228/https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/country/iran/| archive-date=9 March 2020| url-status=live}}</ref>{{Better source|date=March 2020}}\n\n[[Image:3408162 \u0628\u062e\u0634 \u0648\u06cc\u0698\u0647 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0628\u06cc\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0647\u0627\u062c\u0631.jpg|thumb|250px|A patient receiving treatment in a hospital in [[Tehran]]]]\n*27 February: The Ministry of Health reported 126 more new confirmed cases and 7 new deaths.<ref name=\"MOH27FebA\">{{cite web |title=\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0633\u0627\u06cc\u06cc 106 \u0628\u06cc\u0645\u0627\u0631 \u062c\u062f\u06cc\u062f \u06a9\u0648\u0648\u06cc\u062f19 \u062f\u0631 \u06a9\u0634\u0648\u0631 |url=http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=54782&newsview=199991 |website=behdasht.gov |accessdate=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227163707/http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=54782&newsview=199991 |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Iran's Vice President of Iran for Women and Family Affairs, [[Masoumeh Ebtekar]], was diagnosed with COVID-19, as well as the Chairman of the Iranian Parliament's National Security and Foreign Affairs Committee, [[Mojtaba Zonnour|Mojtaba Zolnour]].<ref name=\"Ebtekar\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/high-ranking-iranian-official-catches-coronavirus/1746752 |title=High-ranking Iranian official catches coronavirus |website=www.aa.com.tr |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227161444/https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/high-ranking-iranian-official-catches-coronavirus/1746752 |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/coronavirus-iran-vice-president-masoumeh-ebtekar-test-positive-outbreak-latest-a9363181.html |title=Iran's vice-president diagnosed with coronavirus |date=27 February 2020 |website=The Independent |language=en |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227151952/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/coronavirus-iran-vice-president-masoumeh-ebtekar-test-positive-outbreak-latest-a9363181.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Iran's First Ambassador to the Vatican, {{Interlanguage link|Hadi Khosroshahi|fa|\u0633\u06cc\u062f \u0647\u0627\u062f\u06cc \u062e\u0633\u0631\u0648\u0634\u0627\u0647\u06cc}}, died from COVID-19 infection in Qom.<ref name=\"Ebtekar\" />\n*28 February: the Ministry of Health reported 143 more new confirmed cases and 8 new deaths.<ref name=\"MOH28Feb\"/>\n*29 February: the Ministry of Health reported 205 more new confirmed cases and 9 new deaths. He also reported that 50 more people have recovered.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200039 |title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u060c \u062f\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u0643\u064a |website=behdasht.gov.ir |accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===March 2020===\n[[File:CoViD-19 IR.svg|thumb|left|upright=2|Number of cases (blue) and number of deaths (red) on a [[logarithmic scale]].]]\n\n*1 March: the Ministry of Health reported 385 more new confirmed cases and 11 new deaths. He also reported that 52 more people have recovered, bringing the total number to 175.<ref name=\"Behdasht_523cases_12deaths_2Mar\" />\n*2 March: the Ministry of Health reported 523 more new confirmed cases and 12 new deaths. They also reported that 116 more people have recovered, bringing the total number to 291.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200188|title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u060c \u062f\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u0643\u064a|website=behdasht.gov.ir|accessdate=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303001521/http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200188|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Mohammad Mirmohammadi]], a member of the Expediency Council which advises the [[Supreme Leader of Iran|Supreme Leader]] [[Ali Khamenei]], was reported to have died of the disease.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://time.com/5793379/iran-supreme-leader-adviser-coronavirus/ |title=Adviser to Iranian Supreme Leader Khamenei Dies of Coronavirus |author1=Nasser Karimi |author2=Jon Gambrell |date=2 March 2020 |work=Time |access-date=2 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302154723/https://time.com/5793379/iran-supreme-leader-adviser-coronavirus/ |archive-date=2 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*3 March: the Ministry of Health reported 835 more new confirmed cases and 11 new deaths.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200252|title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u060c \u062f\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u0643\u064a|website=behdasht.gov.ir|accessdate=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310050601/http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200252|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> 23 members of the [[Islamic Consultative Assembly|Iranian Parliament]] were reported to have been infected.<ref name=henley /> More than 54,000 prisoners were temporarily released to prevent the spread of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51723398 |title=Coronavirus: Iran temporarily frees 54,000 prisoners to combat spread |work=BBC News |date=3 March 2020 |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305001254/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51723398 |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The head of emergency medical services, Pirhossein Kolivand, was diagnosed with the disease.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/coronavirus-iran-emergency-medical-services-pirhossein-kolivand-a9371991.html|title=Coronavirus: Iran's head of emergency medical services diagnosed with disease|first=Rory|last=Sullivan|work=The Independent|date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303151942/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/coronavirus-iran-emergency-medical-services-pirhossein-kolivand-a9371991.html|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*4 March: the Ministry of Health reported 586 more new confirmed cases and 15 new deaths. They also reported that 552 people have recovered so far.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200306|title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u060c \u062f\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u0643\u064a|website=behdasht.gov.ir|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n*5 March: The Ministry of Health reported 591 more new confirmed cases and 15 new deaths. They also reported that 739 people had recovered so far.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200330|title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u060c \u062f\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u0643\u064a|website=behdasht.gov.ir|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> {{ill|Mohammad Sadr (diplomat)|lt=Mohammad Sadr|fa|\u0633\u06cc\u062f \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0635\u062f\u0631 (\u062f\u06cc\u067e\u0644\u0645\u0627\u062a)}}, a member of the Expediency Council, had reportedly been infected with coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/05/Iranian-council-member-infected-with-coronavirus-Reports.html |title=Second Khamenei advisor infected with coronavirus in Iran |date=5 March 2020 |accessdate=6 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310050632/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/05/Iranian-council-member-infected-with-coronavirus-Reports.html |archive-date=10 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Akbar Dehghan (head of Qom seminary interpretation staff), Ayatollah Mohsen Habibi (a member of the Supreme Council of Tehran's Seminaries),<ref name=\"Langroudi\"/> Former Ambassador to Syria [[Hossein Sheikholeslam]] died from the disease. Sheikholeslam was also an advisor to the foreign Minister Javad Zarif, and one of the leaders of the group which took [[Iran hostage crisis|hostage]] diplomats and employees of the US embassy in Tehran in 1979.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/former-hostage-taker-of-us-diplomats-dies-of-coronavirus-in-iran/30470975.html |title=Former Hostage Taker Of US Diplomats Dies Of Coronavirus In Iran |work=Radio Farda |date=6 March 2020 |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306151802/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/former-hostage-taker-of-us-diplomats-dies-of-coronavirus-in-iran/30470975.html |archive-date=6 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Subsequently, all government officials were forbidden from international travel, and parliament was indefinitely suspended.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/another-senior-iranian-politician-has-died-of-coronavirus-2020-3?r=US&IR=T |title=Another senior politician has died of coronavirus in Iran, where 8% of the parliament is infected |work=Business Insider |first=David |last=Choi |date=5 March 2020 |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310050641/https://www.businessinsider.com/another-senior-iranian-politician-has-died-of-coronavirus-2020-3?r=US&IR=T |archive-date=10 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[Image:\u0639\u0645\u0644\u06cc\u0627\u062a \u0636\u062f\u0639\u0641\u0648\u0646\u06cc \u0645\u0639\u0627\u0628\u0631 \u0639\u0645\u0648\u0645\u06cc \u0648 \u0634\u0647\u0631\u06cc \u0645\u062d\u0644\u0647 \u0646\u0628\u0631\u062f \u062a\u0647\u0631\u0627\u0646.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Disinfection of [[Piroozi]], Tehran]]\n*6 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1234 more new confirmed cases and 17 new deaths. They also reported that 913 people had recovered so far.\n*7 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1076 more new confirmed cases and 21 new deaths. Elected Member of Parliament [[Fatemeh Rahbar]] died due to coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/iranian-mp-dies-from-coronavirus-tasnim-news-agency-idUSKBN20U0DL |title=Iranian MP dies from coronavirus: Tasnim news agency |date=7 March 2020 |accessdate=7 March 2020 |work=Reuters |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307154240/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/iranian-mp-dies-from-coronavirus-tasnim-news-agency-idUSKBN20U0DL |archive-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Ayatollah {{ill|Reza Mohammadi Langroudi|fa|\u0631\u0636\u0627 \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f\u06cc \u0644\u0646\u06af\u0631\u0648\u062f\u06cc}} also died from the virus.<ref name=\"Langroudi\">{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/07/Two-Iranian-religious-figures-latest-to-die-of-coronavirus-in-Iran.html |title=Two Iranian religious figures latest to die of coronavirus in Iran |date=7 March 2020 |accessdate=7 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315075740/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/07/Two-Iranian-religious-figures-latest-to-die-of-coronavirus-in-Iran.html |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*8 March: the Ministry of Health reported 743 more new confirmed cases and 49 new deaths. They also reported that 2134 people had recovered so far.\n*9 March: the Ministry of Health reported 595 more new confirmed cases and 43 new deaths. They also reported that another 260 people had recovered. {{ill|Esmail Najjar|fa|\u0627\u0633\u0645\u0627\u0639\u06cc\u0644 \u0646\u062c\u0627\u0631}}, the chief of Iran's Crisis Management Organization, was infected with coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/chief-of-iran-s-crisis-management-quarantined-due-to-coronavirus/30477355.html |title=Chief Of Iran's Crisis Management Quarantined Due To Coronavirus |date=9 March 2020 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |publisher=[[Radio Farda]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310050655/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/chief-of-iran-s-crisis-management-quarantined-due-to-coronavirus/30477355.html |archive-date=10 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Former MP [[Mohammad-Reza Rahchamani]] died from the virus.<ref name=\"Rahchamani\">{{cite news|title=Former Iranian MP dies of coronavirus|url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/445916/Former-Iranian-MP-dies-of-coronavirus|date=9 March 2020|accessdate=9 March 2020|newspaper=[[Tehran Times]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310050701/https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/445916/Former-Iranian-MP-dies-of-coronavirus|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> About 70,000 prisoners were temporarily released as coronavirus cases surge.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/iran-temporarily-releases-70000-prisoners-as-coronavirus-cases-surge-idUSKBN20W1E5 |title=Iran temporarily releases 70,000 prisoners as coronavirus cases surge |work=[[Reuters]] |date=9 March 2020 |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310071208/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/iran-temporarily-releases-70000-prisoners-as-coronavirus-cases-surge-idUSKBN20W1E5 |archive-date=10 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Iran's Supreme Leader [[Ali Khamenei]] decided to cancel his [[Nowruz|Persian New Year]] speech which took place every year at the [[Imam Reza shrine]], [[Mashhad]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/09/Iran-s-Khamenei-cancels-Persian-new-year-speech-over-coronavirus-fears.html |title=Iran's Khamenei cancels Persian new year speech over coronavirus fears |work=[[Al Arabiya English]] |date=9 March 2020 |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315075815/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/09/Iran-s-Khamenei-cancels-Persian-new-year-speech-over-coronavirus-fears.html |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Farhad Tazari, the former head of the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps\u2019 Political Bureau, also died of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ifpnews.com/coronavirus-kills-two-more-iranian-politicians|title=Coronavirus Kills Two More Iranian Politicians|work=IFP News|date=9 March 2020|access-date=10 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310152232/https://ifpnews.com/coronavirus-kills-two-more-iranian-politicians|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*10 March: the Ministry of Health reported 881 more new confirmed cases and 54 new deaths. They also reported that another 337 people had recovered. The death toll rose to 291.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://ifpnews.com/coronavirus-kills-record-breaking-number-of-iranians-in-24-hours |title=Coronavirus Kills Record-Breaking Number of Iranians in 24 Hours |website=IFP News |date=10 March 2020 |access-date=11 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311155042/https://ifpnews.com/coronavirus-kills-record-breaking-number-of-iranians-in-24-hours |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*11 March: The Ministry of Health reported 958 more new confirmed cases and 63 new deaths. They also reported that a total of 2,959 patients had recovered so far. Hassan Rouhani, Iran's President, has assumed the chairmanship of the national taskforce on combatting the outbreak of the novel Coronavirus, replacing the Health Minister at the request of lawmakers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ifpnews.com/rouhani-to-chair-irans-taskforce-on-combatting-coronavirus|title=Rouhani to Chair Iran's Taskforce on Combatting Coronavirus|website=IFP News|date=11 March 2020|access-date=11 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312175854/https://ifpnews.com/rouhani-to-chair-irans-taskforce-on-combatting-coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Iran's First Vice President [[Eshaq Jahangiri]] was infected with the virus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news-tunisia.tunisienumerique.com/coronavirus-irans-first-vice-president-jahangiri-infected/ |title=Coronavirus: Iran's first vice president Jahangiri infected |date=11 March 2020 |accessdate=11 March 2020 |publisher=Tunisie Numerique |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312060842/https://news-tunisia.tunisienumerique.com/coronavirus-irans-first-vice-president-jahangiri-infected/ |archive-date=12 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Other two sick officials were [[Ali Asghar Mounesan]], minister of cultural heritage, handicrafts and tourism, and [[Reza Rahmani]], minister of industry, mines and business.<ref name=\"iran-vice-president-ministers-stricken-coronavirus\">{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-vice-president-ministers-stricken-coronavirus-200311155806337.html |title=Iran's vice president and two ministers stricken by coronavirus |date=11 March 2020 |accessdate=11 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Jazeera English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311194200/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-vice-president-ministers-stricken-coronavirus-200311155806337.html |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/iran-vice-president-2-cabinet-members-reportedly-diagnosed-with-coronavirus/ |title=Iran vice president, 2 cabinet members reportedly diagnosed with coronavirus |date=11 March 2020 |accessdate=11 March 2020 |magazine=[[Times of Israel]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312131059/https://www.timesofisrael.com/iran-vice-president-2-cabinet-members-reportedly-diagnosed-with-coronavirus/ |archive-date=12 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n[[Image:13981225000552637198764368440415 \u0647\u0634\u062f\u0627\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u00ab\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627\u06cc\u06cc\u00bb \u062f\u0631 \u0634\u0647\u0631.jpg|thumb|250px|People in [[Shiraz]] wearing facemasks next to a closed market]]\n*12 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,075 more new confirmed cases and 75 new deaths. They also reported that 3,276 people had recovered so far. Member of [[Expediency Discernment Council]] [[Ali Akbar Velayati]] was infected with the virus.<ref name=\"velayati\">{{cite news |title=Top adviser to Iran's supreme leader infected with coronavirus: Tasnim |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-aide/top-adviser-to-irans-supreme-leader-infected-with-coronavirus-tasnim-idUSKBN20Z38J |accessdate=12 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |date=12 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313002146/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-aide/top-adviser-to-irans-supreme-leader-infected-with-coronavirus-tasnim-idUSKBN20Z38J |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Iran requested an emergency load of US$5 billion from the [[International Monetary Fund]] for the first time since the 1960s to help combat the virus outbreak.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/03/12/iran-request-5-billion-emergency-loan-international-monetary/ |title=Iran requests $5 billion emergency loan from International Monetary Fund to fight coronavirus pandemic |first=Roland |last=Oliphant |date=12 March 2020 |work=The Telegraph |access-date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314013011/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/03/12/iran-request-5-billion-emergency-loan-international-monetary/ |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Khamenei said that the virus outbreak may be a \"biological attack\" on Iran.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-12/iran-s-khamenei-says-virus-outbreak-may-be-biological-attack |title=Iran's Khamenei Says Virus Outbreak May Be 'Biological Attack' |first1=Yasna |last1=Haghdoost |first2=Golnar |last2=Motevalli |work=Bloomberg |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323123634/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-12/iran-s-khamenei-says-virus-outbreak-may-be-biological-attack |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*13 March: The Ministry of Health reported 1,289 more new confirmed cases and 85 new deaths. They also reported that 3,529 people had recovered so far. [[Nasser Shabani]], a senior commander of [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps]] (IRGC), has died from the virus.<ref name=\"shabani-dies\">{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/13/Senior-Iranian-IRGC-commander-dies-of-coronavirus-.html |title=Senior Iranian IRGC commander dies of coronavirus |date=13 March 2020 |accessdate=13 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314172342/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/13/Senior-Iranian-IRGC-commander-dies-of-coronavirus-.html |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*14 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,365 more new confirmed cases and 97 new deaths. They also reported that 4,339 people had recovered so far. [[Minoo Mohraz]], a member of committee to combat Coronavirus, tested positive for the virus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/14/Iran-Member-of-committee-to-combat-Coronavirus-tests-positive-for-the-virus.html |title=Iran: Member of committee to combat Coronavirus tests positive for the virus |date=14 March 2020 |accessdate=14 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316012227/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/14/Iran-Member-of-committee-to-combat-Coronavirus-tests-positive-for-the-virus.html |archive-date=16 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*15 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,209 more new confirmed cases and 113 new deaths. They also reported that 4,590 people had recovered so far. [[Hashem Bathaie Golpayegani]], a member of [[Assembly of Experts]], tested positive for the virus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iran Assembly of Experts member infected with coronavirus |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/15/Iran-Assembly-of-Experts-member-infected-with-coronavirus.html |accessdate=15 March 2020 |agency=Al Arabiya English |date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315113238/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/15/Iran-Assembly-of-Experts-member-infected-with-coronavirus.html |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asriran.com/fa/news/718963|title=\u0641\u0631\u06cc\u0628\u0631\u0632 \u0631\u0626\u06cc\u0633 \u062f\u0627\u0646\u0627\u060c \u0627\u0642\u062a\u0635\u0627\u062f\u062f\u0627\u0646\u060c \u0628\u0631 \u0627\u062b\u0631 \u0627\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631\u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a|publisher=Asr Iran|date=16 March 2020|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n*16 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,053 more new confirmed cases and 129 new deaths. They also reported that 4,996 people had recovered so far. [[Hashem Bathaie Golpayegani]] and economist [[Fariborz Raisdana]] died from the virus.<ref name=\"golpayegani-dies\">{{cite news |title=Top Iranian cleric among those tasked with choosing supreme leader succumbs to coronavirus infection |url=https://www.rt.com/news/483203-iran-top-cleric-coronavirus/ |accessdate=16 March 2020 |agency=RT News |date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317040733/https://www.rt.com/news/483203-iran-top-cleric-coronavirus/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*17 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,178 more new confirmed cases and 135 new deaths. They also reported that 5,389 people had recovered so far. [[Sharif University]] published a study over number of possible casualties. Three scenarios were announced: If people cooperate now, Iran will see 120,000 infections and 12,000 deaths before the outbreak is over, if they offer medium cooperation, there will be 300,000 cases and 110,000 deaths. But if people fail to follow any guidance, it could collapse Iran's already strained medical system and there will be 4 million cases and 3.5 million deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|title=Iran warns virus could kill 'millions' in Islamic Republic|date=17 March 2020|website=AP NEWS|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318132446/https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Traditional Persian fire festival [[Chaharshanbe Suri]] were also banned by the government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/iran-bans-fire-festival-celebrations-over-virus/1769048|title=Iran bans fire festival celebrations over virus|website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook India]]|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317180228/https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/iran-bans-fire-festival-celebrations-over-virus/1769048|archive-date=17 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> About 85,000 prisoners were temporarily released due to the coronavirus, and two days later the government announced plans to pardon 11,000 prisoners, including those charged with political crimes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iran frees 85,000 prisoners due to coronavirus, says judiciary spokesman |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/17/Iran-frees-85-000-prisoners-due-to-coronavirus-says-judiciary-spokesman.html |accessdate=18 March 2020 |agency=Al Arabiya English |date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318141153/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/17/Iran-frees-85-000-prisoners-due-to-coronavirus-says-judiciary-spokesman.html |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/iran-to-pardon-10000-including-security-prisoners |title=Iran to pardon 10,000, including 'security' prisoners |first=Patrick |last=Wintour |date=19 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320191918/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/iran-to-pardon-10000-including-security-prisoners |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*18 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,192 more new confirmed cases and 147 new deaths. They also reported that 5,710 people had recovered so far. \n*19 March: the Ministry of Health reported 1,046 more new confirmed cases and 149 new deaths. Former MP [[Hamid Kahram]] died from the coronavirus.<ref name=\"kahram-dies\">{{cite news |title=Former Iran MP Hamid Kahram dies from coronavirus |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/20/Former-Iran-MP-Hamid-Kahram-dies-from-coronavirus.html |accessdate=20 March 2020 |agency=Al Arabiya English |date=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320025009/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/20/Former-Iran-MP-Hamid-Kahram-dies-from-coronavirus.html |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*On 20 March, 1,237 new infections and 149 deaths were reported. Media reports suggested that heavy traffic continued for the Nowruz holiday. A government minister had warned that the crisis might continue for six months if the disease is not brought under control.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/20/iranian-new-year-self-isolate-covid-19 |title=Iranians ignore requests to stay home for new year celebrations |first=Patrick |last=Wintour |date= 20 March 2020 |work=The Guardian }}</ref>\n* On 24 March, a new peak of 1,762 new cases were announced with 122 deaths reported.  President Rouhani said that the number of patients admitted to hospitals in different provinces as well as deaths due to the virus had decreased, which he took to be promising.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/446297/Rouhani-claims-number-of-coronavirus-patients-deaths-decreasing |title=Rouhani claims number of coronavirus patients, deaths decreasing |date=24 March 2020 |work=Tehran Times }}</ref> Iran accused [[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res]] of being spies, and a team they had sent to Iran to help had been ordered to leave the country.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.msf.org/msf-surprised-iran-put-stop-our-covid-19-response |title=MSF \"deeply surprised\" that Iranian authorities put a stop to our COVID-19 response |date=25 March 2020 |work=Medecins Sans Frontieres }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-rejects-foreign-virus-death-toll-nears-2000-200324202829056.html |title=Iran rejects 'foreign' help as virus death toll nears 2,000 |date=24 March 2020|work=Al Jazeera }}</ref>\n* On 25 March, with new cases surpassing 2,000 for the first time, the government warned of a \"second wave\" of infection.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-52039298 |title=Coronavirus: Iran bans internal travel to avert 'second wave'|date=25 March 2020 |work=BBC }}</ref>\n* On 26 March, Iranian Health Ministry announced that 2,389 more people had become infected, with 157 new deaths.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-toll/irans-death-toll-from-coronavirus-climbs-to-2234-ministry-idUSKBN21D18F |title=Iran's death toll from coronavirus climbs to 2,234: ministry |work=Reuters |date= 26 March 2020 }}</ref>\n* On 27 March, daily new cases had increased to 2,926 with 144 deaths.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/03/27/world/middleeast/27reuters-health-coronavirus-iran.html |title=Iran's Death Toll From Coronavirus Rises to 2,378: Health Ministry|agency= Reuters |date=27 March 2020|work=Reuters |via=The New York Times}}</ref> Iranian media reported that nearly 300 people had died and over a thousand became ill due to [[methanol poisoning]] in the belief that drinking the alcohol can kill the virus in the body. [[Associated Press]] gave figures of around 480 deaths and 2,850 others affected.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2020/03/27/world/middleeast/ap-ml-virus-outbreak-iran-a-deadly-drink.html |title=In Iran, False Belief a Poison Fights Virus Kills Hundreds|agency=Associated Press |via=NY Times|date=27 March 2020|access-date=27 March 2020|archive-date=27 March 2020|archive-url=https://archive.is/f7RbN}}</ref> 70 inmates escaped Saqqez [[Prison]] in [[Kurdistan province]].<ref name=riot_iran />\n* On 28 March, the number of new cases exceeded 3,000 for the first time (3,076), with 139 reported new deaths.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/iran-coronavirus-death-toll-rises-to-2-517/1783000 |title=Iran: Coronavirus death toll rises to 2,517first=Ahmet |last=Dursun |date=28 March 2020|work=Analou Agency }}</ref> Prisoners in the [[western Iran]]ian city of [[Hamadan]] rioted against the authorities' refusal to release them in the midst of the coronavirus outbreak. They clashed with [[IRGC]] guards and set a part of the prison on fire with some of them succeeding in escaping.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apa.az/en/asia-news/Iran:-Rebellion-and-fires-in-Hamedan-prison-prisoners-escape-316555|title=Iran: Rebellion and fires in Hamedan prison, prisoners escape|date=29 March 2020|website=apa.az}}</ref> Prisoners in the city of [[Mahabad]], in Iran's [[Kurds|Kurdish]] region, also attempted to escape. Shootout occurred inside the prison; two people were reported killed while dozens managed to escape.<ref>[https://www.avatoday.net/node/9307 More attempts of prison break reported from Iran]</ref>\n* On 29 March, 2,901 new cases and 123 new deaths were announced.<ref name=\"irna-29march\">{{cite news|url=https://en.irna.ir/news/83731895/Official-12-391-COVID19-infected-patients-recovered-in-Iran|title=Official: 12,391 COVID19-infected patients recovered in Iran|work=Islamic Republic News Agency|date=29 March 2020|access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref> President Rouhani defended his government's response to the crisis, and said that according to health experts and doctors in Iran, \"in some provinces, we have passed the peak [of the epidemic] and are on a downward trajectory\".<ref name=\"aljazeera29032020\">{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-coronavirus-deaths-rise-rouhani-hits-criticism-200329113250455.html |title=As Iran coronavirus deaths rise, Rouhani hits back at criticism |date=29 March 2020 |work=Al Jazeera }}</ref>\n*On 30 March, there was a [[Impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on prisons|prison riot]] in the south of the country. 100,000 prisoners have been released as a measure to contain the pandemic, but an estimated 50,000 people are still behind bars, including violent offenders and dual nationals and others with Western ties.<ref name=riot_iran>[https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/jordan-releases-travelers-quarantined-dead-sea-hotels-69867295?cid=clicksource_76_null_headlines_hed Prisoners riot in Iran; Netanyahu goes into self-quarantine] By AMIR VAHDAT and ARON HELLER, Associated Press, 30 Mar 2020</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus outbreak data/Iran medical cases}}\n\n== Government response ==\n[[Image:13981205000415637181505100958241 \u0646\u0634\u0633\u062a \u062e\u0628\u0631\u06cc \u0633\u062e\u0646\u06af\u0648\u06cc \u062f\u0648\u0644\u062a.jpg|thumb|250px|Spokesperson of the Government [[Ali Rabiei]] and Deputy Health Minister [[Iraj Harirchi]] at a press conference. Hours after the conference, it was announced that Harirchi himself tested positive for the virus]]\nOn 22 February 2020, the [[Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance|Ministry of Islamic Culture and Guidance]], announced the cancellation of all concerts and other cultural events for one week.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iranian-doctors-call-for-long-holiday-to-contain-coronavirus-outbreak/30449047.html|title=Iranian Doctors Call For 'Long Holiday' To Contain Coronavirus, As Sixth Victim Dies|website=RFE/RL|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223130155/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iranian-doctors-call-for-long-holiday-to-contain-coronavirus-outbreak/30449047.html|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Health and Medical Education]] also announced the closure of universities, higher educational institutions and schools in several cities and provinces.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-announces-closure-of-universities-schools-to-fight-coronavirus/30449711.html|title=Iran Announces Closure Of Universities, Schools As Coronavirus Death Toll Rises|website=RFE/RL|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223170351/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-announces-closure-of-universities-schools-to-fight-coronavirus/30449711.html|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Sport and Youth (Iran)|Ministry of Sports and Youth]] took steps to cancel sporting events, including football matches.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.varzesh3.com/news/1669982/\u0644\u063a\u0648-\u0647\u0645\u0647-\u0645\u0633\u0627\u0628\u0642\u0627\u062a-\u0648\u0631\u0632\u0634\u06cc-\u0628\u0647-\u0645\u062f\u062a-\u0631\u0648\u0632 |title=\u0644\u063a\u0648 \u0647\u0645\u0647 \u0645\u0633\u0627\u0628\u0642\u0627\u062a \u0648\u0631\u0632\u0634\u06cc \u0628\u0647 \u0645\u062f\u062a \u06f1\u06f0 \u0631\u0648\u0632|website=varzesh3.com|language=Persian|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Defence and Armed Forces Logistics (Iran)|Ministry of Defense and Armed Forces Logistics]] created the first COVID-19 test kit on 23 February.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ir.sputniknews.com/iran/202002235998625-\u062a\u0648\u0644\u06cc\u062f-\u0646\u062e\u0633\u062a\u06cc\u0646-\u06a9\u06cc\u062a-\u062a\u0634\u062e\u06cc\u0635-\u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627-\u062f\u0631-\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646/|title=\u062a\u0648\u0644\u06cc\u062f \u0646\u062e\u0633\u062a\u06cc\u0646 \u06a9\u06cc\u062a \u062a\u0634\u062e\u06cc\u0635 \u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646|agency=Sputnik News Agency|language=fa|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224175254/https://ir.sputniknews.com/iran/202002235998625-%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D9%86%D8%AE%D8%B3%D8%AA%DB%8C%D9%86-%DA%A9%DB%8C%D8%AA-%D8%AA%D8%B4%D8%AE%DB%8C%D8%B5-%D9%88%DB%8C%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Management and Planning Organisation of Iran|Management and Planning Organization]] announced the government has allocated 5&nbsp;trillion rials to combat the virus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jamaran.news/\u0628\u062e\u0634-\u067e\u0631\u0648\u0641\u0627\u06cc\u0644-182/1363201-\u0627\u062e\u062a\u0635\u0627\u0635-\u0645\u06cc\u0644\u06cc\u0627\u0631\u062f-\u062a\u0648\u0645\u0627\u0646-\u0628\u0647-\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a-\u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a-\u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc-\u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647-\u0628\u0627-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627|title=\u0627\u062e\u062a\u0635\u0627\u0635 530 \u0645\u06cc\u0644\u06cc\u0627\u0631\u062f \u062a\u0648\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0647 \u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0627 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627|website=\u067e\u0627\u06cc\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u062e\u0628\u0631\u06cc \u062c\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u2013 \u0627\u0645\u0627\u0645 \u062e\u0645\u06cc\u0646\u06cc \u2013 \u0627\u0646\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u06cc|language=fa|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315091035/https://www.jamaran.news/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%B4-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%81%D8%A7%DB%8C%D9%84-182/1363201-%D8%A7%D8%AE%D8%AA%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%B5-%D9%85%DB%8C%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AF-%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%88%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B4%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7|archive-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[President of Iran|President]] [[Hassan Rouhani]] ordered the [[Ministry of Roads and Urban Development]] to make decisions about public commuting and the [[Ministry of Industry, Mine and Trade]] to build the required medical equipment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.saat24.news/news/484027/\u0631\u0648\u062d\u0627\u0646\u06cc-\u062f\u0633\u062a\u0648\u0631\u0627\u062a-\u0644\u0627\u0632\u0645-\u0631\u0627-\u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc-\u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647-\u0647\u0645\u0647-\u062c\u0627\u0646\u0628\u0647-\u0628\u0627-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627-\u0635\u0627\u062f\u0631|title=\u0631\u0648\u062d\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u062f\u0633\u062a\u0648\u0631\u0627\u062a \u0644\u0627\u0632\u0645 \u0631\u0627 \u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647 \u0647\u0645\u0647\u200c\u062c\u0627\u0646\u0628\u0647 \u0628\u0627 \"\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627\" \u0635\u0627\u062f\u0631 \u06a9\u0631\u062f|date=23 February 2020|website=\u0633\u0627\u0639\u062a24|language=fa|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223183241/https://www.saat24.news/news/484027/%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%85-%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%87-%D9%87%D9%85%D9%87-%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%B1|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPresident Rouhani, however, said on 26 February 2020 that there are no plans to quarantine areas affected by the outbreak, and only individuals would be quarantined.<ref name=quarantine>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51651454 |title=Coronavirus: Iran has no plans to quarantine cities, Rouhani says |work=BBC |date=26 February 2020 |access-date=26 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226194202/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51651454 |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Nevertheless, Iran's Health Ministry said that Friday prayers will not be held in Tehran and areas affected by the outbreak that week.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/saudi-arabia-halts-travel-to-islams-holiest-site-over-virus%2f2020%2f02%2f26%2fc86ec712-5918-11ea-8efd-0f904bdd8057_story.html |title=Iran news agencies report Friday prayers canceled in Tehran |first=Jon |last=Gambrell |agency=Associated Press |via=Washington Post |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227215249/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/saudi-arabia-halts-travel-to-islams-holiest-site-over-virus/2020/02/26/c86ec712-5918-11ea-8efd-0f904bdd8057_story.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 20 February, according to a letter of Iran's health ministry to the governor of Qom, a request was made to \"limit the number of pilgrims at the [[Fatima Masumeh Shrine]] and other religious sites\".<ref name=\"nyt\">{{cite news |title='Recipe for a Massive Viral Outbreak': Iran Emerges as a Worldwide Threat |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/24/world/middleeast/coronavirus-iran.html |website=NYT |accessdate=24 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312121420/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/24/world/middleeast/coronavirus-iran.html |archive-date=12 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, [[Shia]] shrines in Qom remained open for pilgrims to congregate.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/26/middleeast/iran-coronavirus-intl/index.html|title=Iran was already struggling with one crisis. Now it has the worst coronavirus outbreak in the Middle East|author1=Ramin Mostaghim|author2=Mostafa Salem|author3=Tamara Qiblawi|work=CNN|date=26 February 2020|access-date=26 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226200703/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/26/middleeast/iran-coronavirus-intl/index.html|archive-date=26 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The head of Fatima Masumeh shrine encouraged pilgrims to visit the shrine on 27 February: \"We consider this holy shrine to be a place of healing.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20200227-iran-cleric-encourages-visitors-to-qom-religious-sites-despite-coronavirus-fears/ |title=Iran cleric encourages visitors to Qom religious sites, despite coronavirus fears |date=27 February 2020 |work=Middle East Monitor |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303165907/https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20200227-iran-cleric-encourages-visitors-to-qom-religious-sites-despite-coronavirus-fears/ |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe Iranian judiciary spokesman, Gholam Hossein Ismaili said that \"he was activating a range of preventive measures including cutting the number of people being sent to jail and allowing some inmates out on temporary early release.\"<ref name=\"Guard_NZagRatc_possible_COVID19\">{{cite news |first1=Mattha |last1=Busby |first2=Michael |last2=Safi |title=Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe suspected of having coronavirus |url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2020/feb/29/nazanin-zaghari-ratcliffe-family-believe-she-has-coronavirus |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=29 February 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301233032/https://www.theguardian.com/news/2020/feb/29/nazanin-zaghari-ratcliffe-family-believe-she-has-coronavirus |archivedate=1 March 2020 |url-status=live |date=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, [[Iranian Cyber Police]] announced that to stop spreading photos and videos which are untrue and fake on coronavirus, notices were given to 118 people and 24 others were arrested.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0628\u06cc\u0633\u062a \u0648 \u0686\u0647\u0627\u0631 \u0634\u0627\u06cc\u0639\u0647 \u067e\u0631\u0627\u06a9\u0646 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u06cc\u0631 \u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f |url=https://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/961993/\u06f2\u06f4-\u0634\u0627\u06cc\u0639\u0647-\u067e\u0631\u0627\u06a9\u0646-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627-\u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633-\u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u06cc\u0631-\u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f |website=www.tabnak.ir |accessdate=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303042943/https://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/961993/%DB%B2%DB%B4-%D8%B4%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B9%D9%87-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%A7%DA%A9%D9%86-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D9%88%DB%8C%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%DA%AF%DB%8C%D8%B1-%D8%B4%D8%AF%D9%86%D8%AF |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> These indictments were considered vague by [[Article 19]],<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646: \u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0632 \u0628\u0647 \u06af\u0631\u062f\u0634 \u0622\u0632\u0627\u062f \u0627\u0637\u0644\u0627\u0639\u0627\u062a \u0631\u0627 \u0645\u0647\u0645 \u062a\u0631 \u0645\u06cc\u200c\u06a9\u0646\u062f |url=https://www.article19.org/fa/resources/iran-coronavirus-crisis-highlights-need-for-the-free-flow-of-information/ |website=ARTICLE 19 |accessdate=6 March 2020 |language=fa-IR |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306205645/https://www.article19.org/fa/resources/iran-coronavirus-crisis-highlights-need-for-the-free-flow-of-information/ |archive-date=6 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> and the government's attempt to control the information flow.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n[[Administrative and Recruitment Affairs Organization]] ruled that [[telecommuting]] of government employees would be permissible.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.asriran.com/fa/news/716947/\u0628\u062e\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647%E2%80%8C-\u0628\u0647-\u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u0627\u0647-\u0647\u0627\u06cc-\u0627\u062c\u0631\u0627\u06cc\u06cc-\u062f\u0648\u0631\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06cc-\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06a9\u0646\u0627\u0646-\u0628\u0644\u0627\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0639-\u0627\u0633\u062a |title= \u0628\u062e\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647\u200c \u0628\u0647 \u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0627\u062c\u0631\u0627\u06cc\u06cc: \u062f\u0648\u0631\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06cc \u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06a9\u0646\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0644\u0627\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0639 \u0627\u0633\u062a |accessdate= 3 March 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200304160526/https://www.asriran.com/fa/news/716947/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%B4%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%87%E2%80%8C-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%DA%AF%D8%A7%D9%87-%D9%87%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%AC%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%DA%A9%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%DA%A9%D8%A7%D8%B1%DA%A9%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA |archive-date= 4 March 2020 |url-status= live }}</ref> Corona National Anti-Virus Headquarters ordered the academic organizations to launch [[learning management systems]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.ilna.news/\u0628\u062e\u0634-\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646-\u0647\u0627-15/880494-\u0631\u0627\u0647-\u0627\u0646\u062f\u0627\u0632\u06cc-\u06a9\u0645\u067e\u06cc\u0646-\u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634-\u0647\u0627\u06cc-\u0645\u062c\u0627\u0632\u06cc-\u0631\u0627\u06cc\u06af\u0627\u0646-\u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc-\u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647-\u0628\u0627-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 |title= \u0631\u0627\u0647\u200c\u0627\u0646\u062f\u0627\u0632\u06cc \u06a9\u0645\u067e\u06cc\u0646 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u062c\u0627\u0632\u06cc \u0631\u0627\u06cc\u06af\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0627 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 |accessdate= 3 March 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200315113600/https://www.ilna.news/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%B4-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%87%D8%A7-15/880494-%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C-%DA%A9%D9%85%D9%BE%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%A2%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B2%D8%B4-%D9%87%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C-%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C%DA%AF%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7 |archive-date= 15 March 2020 |url-status= live }}</ref>\n\nOn 2 March 2020, the government announced plans to mobilise 300,000 soldiers and volunteers to combat the spread of the virus, as well as deploying drones and water cannon to disinfect streets.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-mobilizes-300-000-people-and-deploys-drones-and-water-cannon-to-halt-the-spread-of-coronavirus-11583157765 |title=Iran Mobilizes 300,000 Teams and Deploys Drones and Water Cannon to Halt the Spread of Coronavirus |first1=Aresu |last1=Eqbali |first2=Isabel |last2=Coles |date=2 March 2020 |work=Wall Street Journal |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303152213/https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-mobilizes-300-000-people-and-deploys-drones-and-water-cannon-to-halt-the-spread-of-coronavirus-11583157765 |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The government created an application and a website to combat the outbreak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://digiato.com/article/2020/03/04/\u0627\u067e\u0644\u06cc\u06a9\u06cc\u0634\u0646-\u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647-\u0628\u0627-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627-\u0639\u0631\u0636\u0647-\u0634\u062f\u061b-\u0627\u0632-\u0627\u0646/|title=\u0633\u0627\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0647 \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0627 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0639\u0631\u0636\u0647 \u0634\u062f\u061b \u0627\u0632 \u0627\u0646\u062c\u0627\u0645 \u062a\u0633\u062a\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0627\u0648\u0644\u06cc\u0647 \u062a\u0627 \u0648\u06cc\u062f\u06cc\u0648\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634\u06cc|website=\u062f\u06cc\u062c\u06cc\u0627\u062a\u0648|accessdate=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315113431/https://digiato.com/article/2020/03/04/%D8%A7%D9%BE%D9%84%DB%8C%DA%A9%DB%8C%D8%B4%D9%86-%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%B6%D9%87-%D8%B4%D8%AF%D8%9B-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%A7%D9%86/|archive-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAs confirmed cases mounted, Iran's health minister announced on 5 March 2020 that checkpoints would be placed between cities to limit travel, and schools and universities closed until the start of the holiday for Persian new year [[Nowruz]] on 20 March 2020. Citizens were also advised to avoid using banknotes.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51760563|title=Coronavirus: Iran limits travel and urges banknote avoidance|date=5 March 2020|work=BBC|access-date=6 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306115643/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51760563|archive-date=6 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Major General [[Hossein Salami|Salami]], Commander of the [[Islamic Revolution Guards Corps]], stated \"Iran is currently engaged in [[biological warfare]] and will definitely win the war\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2020/03/05/2217376/iran-involved-in-biological-warfare-irgc-chief/amp|title=Iran Involved in Biological Warfare: IRGC Chief - Politics news|website=Tasnim News Agency|language=en|access-date=6 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307051241/https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2020/03/05/2217376/iran-involved-in-biological-warfare-irgc-chief/amp|archive-date=7 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The government has indicated that it may use force to limit travel between cities.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/06/chinese-schools-reopen-as-coronavirus-cases-in-europe-continue-to-rise |title=Iran threatens use of force to restrict spread of coronavirus |author1=Sam Jones |author2=Patrick Wintour |date=6 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306123813/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/06/chinese-schools-reopen-as-coronavirus-cases-in-europe-continue-to-rise |archive-date=6 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March 2020, around 70,000 prisoners were temporarily released from prisons due to the outbreak ostensibly to limit the further spread of the disease within prisons.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/italy-coronavirus-toll-soars-north-sealed-live-updates-200308235426110.html |title=Iran releases 70,000 prisoners as toll rises: Live updates |first1=Kate |last1=Mayberry |first2=Virginia |last2=Pietromarchi |work=Al Jazeera |date=9 March 2020 |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309135638/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/italy-coronavirus-toll-soars-north-sealed-live-updates-200308235426110.html |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> 85,000 prisoners including political prisoners were released in total by 17 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-iran-frees-85-000-prisoners-to-combat-spread-of-covid-19-11958783 |title=Iran temporarily frees 85,000 from jail, including political prisoners, amid coronavirus |first=Parisa |last=Hafezi |date=17 March 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317144133/https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-iran-frees-85-000-prisoners-to-combat-spread-of-covid-19-11958783 |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March 2020, plan to clear streets, shops and public places in Iran by the Revolutionary Guards was announced. In addition, 1,000 fixed and mobile detection clinics would be set up, the army would work alongside medical staff as well as producing face masks and gloves, and army beds would be made available for patients.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/13/revolutionary-guards-enforce-coronavirus-controls-iran |title=Revolutionary Guards to enforce coronavirus controls in Iran |first=Patrick |last=Wintour=13 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314135322/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/13/revolutionary-guards-enforce-coronavirus-controls-iran |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Iranian football player [[Mohammad Mokhtari (footballer)|Mohammad Mokhtari]] who on 10 March had posted on Instagram, criticising the authorities\u2019 handling of the coronavirus outbreak was arrested by the [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Iran arrests footballer over coronavirus Instagram posts |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/13/Iran-arrests-footballer-over-coronavirus-Instagram-posts-.html |accessdate=13 March 2020 |agency=[[Al Arabiya English]] |date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314152214/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/13/Iran-arrests-footballer-over-coronavirus-Instagram-posts-.html |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 14 March, he was released after offering expressions of regret.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/965850/%DA%A9%D8%A7%D9%BE%DB%8C%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B4-%DA%AF%DB%8C%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A2%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%AF-%D8%B4%D8%AF |title=\u06a9\u0627\u067e\u06cc\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u062f\u0627\u0645\u0627\u0634 \u06af\u06cc\u0644\u0627\u0646 \u0622\u0632\u0627\u062f \u0634\u062f |work=Tabnak |date=14 March 2020 |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315165920/https://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/965850/%DA%A9%D8%A7%D9%BE%DB%8C%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B4-%DA%AF%DB%8C%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A2%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%AF-%D8%B4%D8%AF |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIran's President [[Hassan Rouhani]] wrote public letter to world leaders asking for help, saying that his country doesn't have access to international markets due to the [[United States sanctions against Iran]].<ref>{{cite news |title=U.S. sanctions 'severely hamper' Iran coronavirus fight, Rouhani says |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/us-sanctions-severely-hamper-iran-coronavirus-fight-rouhani-idUSKBN2110HL |agency=Reuters |date=14 March 2020 |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319011538/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/us-sanctions-severely-hamper-iran-coronavirus-fight-rouhani-idUSKBN2110HL |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March 2020, in order to prevent the spread of coronavirus, Fatima Masumeh Shrine, Jamkaran Mosque in Qom, and Imam Reza Shrine in Mashhad were closed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/covid-19-irans-holiest-sites-closing-to-visitors/1768192l|title=COVID-19: Iran's holiest sites closing to visitors|website=AA news|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref> Following this announcement, some people protested to enter the shrine but they were driven out of the shrine by servants and the doors were closed again.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.farsnews.ir/qom/news/13981226001206/\u0648\u0631\u0648\u062f-\u063a\u06cc\u0631\u0642\u0627\u0646\u0648\u0646\u06cc-\u0639\u062f\u0647%E2%80%8C\u0627\u06cc-\u0628\u0647-\u062d\u0631\u0645-\u062d\u0636\u0631\u062a-\u0645\u0639\u0635\u0648\u0645\u0647-\u0633--\u0628\u0627-\u062a\u0644\u0627\u0634-\u062e\u062f\u0627\u0645-\u062f\u0631\u0628%E2%80%8C\u0647\u0627\u06cc-\u062d\u0631\u0645 |title=\u0648\u0631\u0648\u062f \u063a\u06cc\u0631\u0642\u0627\u0646\u0648\u0646\u06cc \u0639\u062f\u0647\u200c\u0627\u06cc \u0628\u0647 \u062d\u0631\u0645 \u062d\u0636\u0631\u062a \u0645\u0639\u0635\u0648\u0645\u0647 (\u0633)|website=Fars news|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://time.com/5804546/iran-shiite-storm-coronavirus/ |title=Shiite Hardliners in Iran Storm 2 Shrines That Were Closed to Stop Coronavirus Spread |first=Jon |last=GambrellA |agency=AP |date=17 March 2020 |via=Time |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317140841/https://time.com/5804546/iran-shiite-storm-coronavirus/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March the government warned that \"millions\" might die from the coronavirus if people keep ignoring health guidelines and continue traveling. 90% of the 18,000 coronavirus cases in the Middle East have taken place in Iran; 988 people have died in the country.<ref>{{cite web|website=AP|title=Iran warns virus could kill 'millions' in Islamic Republic|author1=NASSER KARIMI|author2=JON GAMBRELL|date=17 March 2020|url=https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318132446/https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus pandemic 'could kill millions' in Iran |work=AlJazeera |date=16 May 2020 |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-pandemic-kill-millions-iran-200317135500255.html |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317222216/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-pandemic-kill-millions-iran-200317135500255.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe head of the Medical Council of the Islamic Republic of Iran, Dr. Mohammad Reza Zafarghandi, said on 18 March that 22 million Iranians had been screened and that the condition of a million and a half is being monitored. He also said the numbers given by the Health Ministry are those of confirmed cases, adding, \"The reality is the real numbers are higher than the [reported] numbers.\"\n<ref>{{cite web|title=Iran medical council says coronavirus crisis still developing |url=https://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2020/03/iran-medical-council-coronavirus-peak.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320173253/https://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2020/03/iran-medical-council-coronavirus-peak.html |archivedate=2020-03-20|date=20 March 2020 }}</ref>\nOn 23 March 2020, Iran's [[Supreme Leader of Iran|Supreme Leader]] Ayatollah [[Ali Khamenei]] said that the US created \"a special version\" of the virus that was affecting the country.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Iran's leader suggests US cooked up 'special version' of virus to target country |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/iran-coronavirus-us-target-country-special-version-covid19-a9417206.html |work=The Independent |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324095310/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/iran-coronavirus-us-target-country-special-version-covid19-a9417206.html |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, President Rouhani announced that the half of all government employees would work remotely at home.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-health-coronavirus-iran/half-of-iranian-government-employees-to-work-remotely-amid-coronavirus-rouhani-idUKKBN21B0SZ |title=Half of Iranian government employees to work remotely amid coronavirus - Rouhani |date=24 March 2020|work=Reuters }}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March 2020, the government warned that Iran may be facing a second wave of coronavirus outbreak because people were ignoring guidance on travelling during the Nowruz holidays, and banned all new trips between cities.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-wave/iran-warns-of-second-wave-of-coronavirus-idUSKBN21C1VT |title=Iran warns of second wave of coronavirus |date=25 March 2020 |work=Reuters |first= Parisa|last= Hafezi}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March 2020, President Rouhani announced that 20% of the country's annual budget would be allocated to fight the virus.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2020/03/28/2232142/iran-allocates-20-of-annual-budget-to-coronavirus-battle |title=Iran Allocates 20% of Annual Budget to Coronavirus Battle |work=Tasnim News Agency |date=28 March 2020}}</ref> The following day, he defended against criticisms of the government's response to the outbreak, saying that he needed to weigh protecting the country economy that was already affected by US sanctions while fighting the worst outbreak of the region.<ref name=\"aljazeera29032020\"/>\n\n==International spread and travel restrictions==\n{{Further|Travel restrictions related to the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n===February 2020===\n[[Image:Imported COVID-19 Cases from Iran.svg|thumb|250px|World countries with [[COVID-19]] cases linked to Iranian [[Disease cluster|clusters]]]]\nOn 20 February, a SARS-CoV-2 confirmed case was reported for a woman in her 30s who had arrived in [[Canada]] from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bc.ctvnews.ca/b-c-s-new-coronavirus-case-is-woman-who-recently-returned-from-iran-1.4821112|title=B.C.'s new coronavirus case is woman who recently returned from Iran|last=Holliday|first=Ian|date=20 February 2020|website=British Columbia|language=en|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221134501/https://bc.ctvnews.ca/b-c-s-new-coronavirus-case-is-woman-who-recently-returned-from-iran-1.4821112|archive-date=21 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 25 February, a woman in her 60s, and the next day her husband, who was also in his 60s, tested positive for SARS-CoV-2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cp24.com/news/toronto-husband-of-ontario-s-fifth-covid-19-case-test-positive-for-virus-1.4829825|title=Toronto husband of Ontario's fifth COVID-19 case test positive for virus|last=Herhalt|first=Chris|website=cp24|date=27 February 2020|language=en|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227133459/https://www.cp24.com/news/toronto-husband-of-ontario-s-fifth-covid-19-case-test-positive-for-virus-1.4829825|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 February, [[Lebanon]] confirmed the first COVID-19 case, a 45-year-old woman travelling from [[Qom]], [[Iran]] was admitted to a hospital in [[Beirut]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://arab.news/9byac|title=Lebanon confirms first coronavirus case as death toll hits 4 in Iran|date=21 February 2020|website=Arab News|access-date=21 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://time.com/5789360/iran-coronavirus-death-toll/|title=Iran COVID-19 Death Toll Reaches 8, With 43 Confirmed Infection Cases|date=23 February 2020|website=Time|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225145921/https://time.com/5789360/iran-coronavirus-death-toll/|archive-date=25 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 February, [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] suspended flights to and from Iran.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://agenda.ge/en/news/2020/558 |title=Georgia suspends direct flights with Iran amid coronavirus outbreak |work=Agenda.ge |date=23 February 2020 |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303134819/https://agenda.ge/en/news/2020/558 |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On the same day, [[Pakistan]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.geo.tv/latest/273901-pakistan-seals-taftan|title=Pakistan seals Taftan border after coronavirus situation deteriorates in Iran|date=23 February 2020|website=geo.tv|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223165746/https://www.geo.tv/latest/273901-pakistan-seals-taftan|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Turkey]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-turkey/turkey-shuts-iran-border-halts-flights-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKCN20H0GH|title=Turkey shuts Iran border, halts flights due to coronavirus|date=23 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223203508/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-turkey/turkey-shuts-iran-border-halts-flights-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKCN20H0GH|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Afghanistan]], and [[Armenia]] closed their land borders with Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/amp/news/2020/02/neighbours-close-borders-iran-virus-concerns-rise-200223160135283.html|title=Neighbours close borders with Iran as virus concerns rise|website=www.aljazeera.com|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224050602/https://www.aljazeera.com/amp/news/2020/02/neighbours-close-borders-iran-virus-concerns-rise-200223160135283.html|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Afghanistan stopped all forms of travel to and from Iran with three suspected cases reported, while Turkey stopped all incoming flights from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/23/turkey-and-pakistan-close-borders-with-iran-over-coronavirus-deaths|title=Turkey and Pakistan close borders with Iran over coronavirus deaths|first=Patrick|last=Wintour|date=23 February 2020|via=www.theguardian.com|access-date=25 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225224333/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/23/turkey-and-pakistan-close-borders-with-iran-over-coronavirus-deaths|archive-date=25 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.arabnews.com/node/1632051/world |title=Pakistan, Turkey, Armenia close Iranian border, Afghanistan bans travel over coronavirus fears |first1=Naimat |last1=Khan |first2=Sayed |last2=Salahuddin |date=27 February 2020 |work=Arab News |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225205628/https://www.arabnews.com/node/1632051/world |archive-date=25 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 24 February, [[Iraq]], [[Kuwait]], [[Oman]], [[Tajikistan]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/tajikistan-suspends-flights-to-iran-over-coronavirus/30451515.html |title=Tajikistan Suspends Flights To Iran Over Coronavirus |date=24 February 2020 |work=Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty |access-date=28 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228225220/https://www.rferl.org/a/tajikistan-suspends-flights-to-iran-over-coronavirus/30451515.html |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> restricted and suspended all flights from and to Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/kuwait-bahrain-announce-first-covid-19-cases-12464358|title=Kuwait, Bahrain, Iraq report coronavirus cases linked to Iran|website=channelnewsasia.com|date=24 February 2020|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224203107/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/world/kuwait-bahrain-announce-first-covid-19-cases-12464358|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref Name= oman>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-oman/oman-reports-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus-halts-flights-to-iran-tv-idUSKCN20I1LL|title=Oman reports first two cases of coronavirus, halts flights to Iran: TV|website=Reuters|date=24 February 2020|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224203107/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-oman/oman-reports-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus-halts-flights-to-iran-tv-idUSKCN20I1LL|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The citizens of the United Arab Emirates were banned from traveling to Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-02-24/kuwait-bahrain-report-cases-of-coronavirus-linked-to-iran|title=U.A.E. Bans Citizens From Iran Travel as Virus Cases Climb|website=Bloomberg|date=24 February 2020|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224103359/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-02-24/kuwait-bahrain-report-cases-of-coronavirus-linked-to-iran|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Armenia]] also suspended flights to Iran but scheduled flights to repatriate its citizens from Iran.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/armenia-coronavirus-repatriate-citizens-iran/30453491.html |title=Armenia To Repatriate Citizens From Iran Amid Coronavirus Outbreak |date=25 February 2020 |work=Radio Free Europe Radio Liberty |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303042815/https://www.rferl.org/a/armenia-coronavirus-repatriate-citizens-iran/30453491.html |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Neighbouring countries Kuwait, Iraq and [[Bahrain]] announced that it recorded their first coronavirus cases from people who came from Iran.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-gulf-idUSKCN20I0PB|title=Kuwait, Bahrain, Iraq report coronavirus cases linked to Iran|date=24 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224143132/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-gulf-idUSKCN20I0PB|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> According to the report of Oman's Health Ministry, there are two Omani women who visited Iran and now infected with the coronavirus.<ref Name= oman/>\n\nOn 26 February, [[Pakistan]] announced two persons had been diagnosed with COVID-19, one of them known to have visited Iran.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200226-pakistan-confirms-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus|title=Pakistan confirms first two cases of coronavirus|date=26 February 2020|work=France 24|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226203500/https://www.france24.com/en/20200226-pakistan-confirms-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus|archive-date=26 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>[[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] confirmed the first COVID-19 case, a 50-year-old Georgian man who returned from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://civil.ge/archives/340246|title=Georgia Confirms First Case of Coronavirus|date=26 February 2020|website=Civil.ge|language=en-US|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227050210/https://civil.ge/archives/340246|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> China confirmed a man in [[Zhongwei]], [[Ningxia]], who returned from Iran, tested positive for SARS-CoV-2.<ref>{{cite web |author1=\u65b0\u4eac\u62a5 |title=\u5b81\u590f\u53d1\u73b01\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u578b\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b \u6025\u5bfb\u5bc6\u5207\u63a5\u89e6\u8005 |url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/02/26/695546.html |language=zh |access-date=1 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226131611/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/02/26/695546.html |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Kazakhstan]] announced a plan to stop flights to and from Iran starting 1 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/world-braces-for-spread-of-new-virus-as-more-countries-report-first-cases/30455787.html |title=Kazakhstan Suspending Flights To Iran Over Coronavirus; Russia Issues Travel Warning |date=26 February 2020 |work=Radio Farda |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227160356/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/world-braces-for-spread-of-new-virus-as-more-countries-report-first-cases/30455787.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 27 February, Estonia confirmed the first COVID-19 case, an Iranian citizen living in [[Estonia]] who returned from Iran.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.err.ee/1057196/first-coronavirus-case-found-in-estonia |title=First Coronavirus case found in Estonia |date=27 February 2020 |publisher=ERR News |location=Estonia |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227065704/https://news.err.ee/1057196/first-coronavirus-case-found-in-estonia |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Kuwait]] confirmed 43 cases of COVID-19, all of them involved people who had travelled to Iran in February.<ref>{{cite news|author=Sara Al Shurafa|url=https://gulfnews.com/world/gulf/kuwait/kuwait-confirms-43-cases-of-coronavirus-all-coming-from-iran-1.1582789585309|title=Kuwait confirms 43 cases of coronavirus, all coming from Iran|date=27 February 2020|work=Gulf News|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227105047/https://gulfnews.com/world/gulf/kuwait/kuwait-confirms-43-cases-of-coronavirus-all-coming-from-iran-1.1582789585309|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Germany]], [[Norway]], [[Sweden]] and [[Spain]] also confirmed new cases involving individuals with previous travels to Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20200227142333-5k62k/|title=Lebanon health ministry confirms third case of coronavirus, NNA reports|last=Foundation|first=Thomson Reuters|website=news.trust.org|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227153900/https://news.trust.org/item/20200227142333-5k62k/|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.swr.de/swraktuell/rheinland-pfalz/kaiserslautern/Neuer-Fall-in-Rheinland-Pfalz-Coronavirus-bei-Patienten-in-Kaiserslautern-festgestellt,corona-kaiserslautern-100.html|title=Coronavirus bei Patient in Kaiserslautern festgestellt|last=Aktuell|first=S. W. R.|last2=Aktuell|first2=S. W. R.|website=swr.online|language=de|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227170424/https://www.swr.de/s