ms first coronavirus case |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=28 February 2020 |via=The Guardian |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229001239/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/28/new-zealand-confirms-first-coronavirus-case |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://eng.belta.by/society/view/belarus-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-128580-2020/ |title=Belarus confirms first case of coronavirus |date=28 February 202 |work=BelTa |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228223501/https://eng.belta.by/society/view/belarus-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-128580-2020/ |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> New Zealand announced temporary restrictions on people travelling from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/119899280/ministry-of-health-gives-latest-update-on-novel-coronavirus|title=Coronavirus: First case of virus in New Zealand|website=Stuff|language=en|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228171221/https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/119899280/ministry-of-health-gives-latest-update-on-novel-coronavirus|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Malaysia set up separate immigration lanes for travellers from countries with major COVID-19 outbreaks including Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/coronavirus-malaysia-bars-south-korea-travellers-covid-19-12480676|title=COVID-19: Malaysia bars travellers from South Korea, confirms 2 new cases|website=CNA|language=en|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229012254/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asia/coronavirus-malaysia-bars-south-korea-travellers-covid-19-12480676|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The United States [[Centers for Disease Control and Prevention|Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)]] upgraded the status of Iran to level 3 (avoid non-essential travels due to widespread community transmission).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wwwnc.cdc.gov/travel/notices/warning/coronavirus-iran|title=Coronavirus in Iran - Warning - Level 3, Avoid Nonessential Travel - Travel Health Notices {{!}} Travelers' Health {{!}} CDC|website=wwwnc.cdc.gov|access-date=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 February, [[Australia]] announced a ban on foreigners arriving directly from Iran, and required them to stay in a third country for 14 days before entering Australia. A woman returning from Iran had also tested positive for the virus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-02-29/australia-announces-iran-travel-ban/12013884 |title=Australia announces Iran travel ban amid COVID-19 coronavirus outbreak |first=Dan |last=Conifer |date=29 February 2020 |work=ABC |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229073205/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-02-29/australia-announces-iran-travel-ban/12013884 |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Azerbaijan]] later closed its border with Iran as two Azeri citizens were confirmed to have been infected in Iran.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-iran-azerbaijan/azerbaijan-closes-border-with-iran-over-coronavirus-concerns-idUSKBN20N0MY |title=Azerbaijan shuts border with Iran over coronavirus concern |date=29 February 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=1 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301055729/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-iran-azerbaijan/azerbaijan-closes-border-with-iran-over-coronavirus-concerns-idUSKBN20N0MY |archive-date=1 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> In [[Qatar]], the first infection in a citizen evacuated from Iran was reported.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/qatar-reports-coronavirus-case-citizen-iran-200229144225648.html |title=Qatar reports first coronavirus case in citizen who was in Iran |date=29 February 2020 |work=Al Jazeera |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229165654/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/02/qatar-reports-coronavirus-case-citizen-iran-200229144225648.html |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===March 2020===\n[[Image:13981214000744637189356214810969 \u0646\u0634\u0633\u062a \u0645\u062f\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0634\u0647\u0631\u06cc \u0628\u0627 \u0646\u0645\u0627\u06cc\u0646\u062f\u06af\u0627\u0646 \u0633\u0627\u0632\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u062c\u0647\u0627\u0646\u06cc.jpg|thumb|250px|[[World Health Organization]] representatives holding joint meeting with Tehran administrators]]\nOn 1 March 2020, Armenia announced its first case of coronavirus infection, identified in a man who had returned from Iran.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/armenia-identifies-first-coronavirus-man-returning-iran/30462231.html |title=Armenia Identifies First Coronavirus Case As Man Returning From Iran |date=1 March 2020 |work=Radio Free Europe Radio Liberty |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303092218/https://www.rferl.org/a/armenia-identifies-first-coronavirus-man-returning-iran/30462231.html |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 2 March 2020, [[Sweden]] announced that it had suspended flights operated by [[Iran Air]], the first country to ban flights by the airline.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thelocal.se/20200302/sweden-bans-flights-from-iran-over-coronavirus-fears |title=Sweden halts flights from Iran over coronavirus fears |work=The Local Sweden |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303140158/https://www.thelocal.se/20200302/sweden-bans-flights-from-iran-over-coronavirus-fears |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 4 March 2020, Thailand declared that people travelling from Iran must be quarantined for 14 days after arriving with no exception.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mgronline.com/qol/detail/9630000021535|title=\"\u0e2d\u0e19\u0e38\u0e17\u0e34\u0e19\" \u0e40\u0e0b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e01\u0e32\u0e28 \u0e2a\u0e18.\u0e01\u0e33\u0e2b\u0e19\u0e14 9 \u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e40\u0e17\u0e28\u0e40\u0e1b\u0e47\u0e19\u0e40\u0e02\u0e15\u0e15\u0e34\u0e14\u0e42\u0e23\u0e04\u0e15\u0e34\u0e14\u0e15\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e2d\u0e31\u0e19\u0e15\u0e23\u0e32\u0e22 \u0e17\u0e38\u0e01\u0e04\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48\u0e40\u0e14\u0e34\u0e19\u0e17\u0e32\u0e07\u0e21\u0e32\u0e15\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e01\u0e31\u0e01\u0e15\u0e31\u0e27 14 \u0e27\u0e31\u0e19 \u0e2a\u0e01\u0e31\u0e14\u0e42\u0e04\u0e27\u0e34\u0e14-19|date=4 March 2020|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304074612/https://mgronline.com/qol/detail/9630000021535|archive-date=4 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Iraq]] and [[Azerbaijan]] stopped letting trucks and imports coming from Iran to enter this country, earlier on 29 February Azerbaijan had closed its borders to the people coming from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/azerbaijan-and-iraq-close-borders-to-imports-from-iran/30470820.html|title=Azerbaijan And Iraq Close Borders To Imports From Iran|website=RFE/RL|accessdate=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306152239/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/azerbaijan-and-iraq-close-borders-to-imports-from-iran/30470820.html|archive-date=6 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 March, [[India]] Delhi confirmed a case of a citizen who recently travelled to Iran.\n[[Thailand]] announced the 46th and 47th confirmed cases of the country, a 22-year-old Chinese and 20-year-old Thai, who had recently travelled to Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pr.moph.go.th/?url=pr/detail/2/04/139480|title=\u0e23\u0e32\u0e22\u0e07\u0e32\u0e19\u0e02\u0e48\u0e32\u0e27\u0e01\u0e23\u0e13\u0e35\u0e44\u0e27\u0e23\u0e31\u0e2a\u0e42\u0e04\u0e42\u0e23\u0e19\u0e32 2019 (COVID-19) \u0e1b\u0e23\u0e30\u0e08\u0e33\u0e27\u0e31\u0e19\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48 5 \u0e21\u0e35\u0e19\u0e32\u0e04\u0e21 2563|trans-title=Report of COVID-19 situation in Thailand, 5 March 2020|language=Thai|via=[[Ministry of Public Health (Thailand)|Ministry of Public Health, Thailand]]|date=5 March 2020|access-date=25 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315080632/https://pr.moph.go.th/?url=pr%2Fdetail%2F2%2F04%2F139480|archive-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March 2020, [[Russia]] announced that it will temporary ban visitors arriving from Iran starting 7 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/russia-closes-border-with-iran-over-coronavirus-fears/1757573 |title=Russia closes border with Iran over coronavirus fears |first=Elena |last=Teslova |date=7 March 2020 |work=Anadolu Agency |access-date=8 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307191959/https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/russia-closes-border-with-iran-over-coronavirus-fears/1757573 |archive-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March 2020, Iran has been recognized as a point of spreading coronavirus to other countries. All of Iran's neighboring states have put some kind of limitations or closed their borders with Iran.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iranair-flights-to-europe-suspended-due-to-restrictions-imposed-coronavirus/30475819.html |title=IranAir Says All Flights To Europe Suspended Due To 'Restrictions' Imposed |publisher=En.radiofarda.com |date=8 March 2020 |accessdate=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312113259/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iranair-flights-to-europe-suspended-due-to-restrictions-imposed-coronavirus/30475819.html |archive-date=12 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Mujib |last=Mashal |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/24/world/middleeast/coronavirus-iran.html |title='Recipe for a Massive Viral Outbreak': Iran Emerges as a Worldwide Threat |publisher=Nytimes.com |date= |accessdate=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312121420/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/24/world/middleeast/coronavirus-iran.html |archive-date=12 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[Shanghai]] confirmed four imported cases from Iran.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wsjkw.sh.gov.cn/xwfb/20200305/32478ccd37ec4e4c8b6fc4082d5d6252.html|title=\u4eca\u59290-12\u65f6\uff0c\u4e0a\u6d77\u65b0\u589e1\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u578b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|date=5 March 2020|accessdate=6 March 2020|publisher=Shanghai Municipal Health Commission}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wsjkw.sh.gov.cn/xwfb/20200306/4bda30d1a7334e819feb2c58d040a744.html|title=\u4eca\u59290-12\u65f6\uff0c\u4e0a\u6d77\u65b0\u589e3\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u578b\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72b6\u75c5\u6bd2\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b|date=6 March 2020|accessdate=6 March 2020|publisher=Shanghai Municipal Health Commission|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324144734/http://wsjkw.sh.gov.cn/xwfb/20200306/4bda30d1a7334e819feb2c58d040a744.html|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=dead}}</ref> The Chinese province of [[Gansu]] also confirmed 25 imported cases from Iran, who had travelled in the charters.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/84639.html|title=\u7518\u8083\u65b0\u589e11\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u7d2f\u8ba1\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b102\u4f8b|date=5 March 2020|accessdate=6 March 2020|publisher=Gansu Provincial Health Commission}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/84677.html|title=\u7518\u8083\u65b0\u589e17\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e \u7d2f\u8ba1\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b28\u4f8b|date=6 March 2020|accessdate=6 March 2020|publisher=Gansu Provincial Health Commission}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/84679.html|title=\u7518\u8083\u65b0\u589e1\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e \u7d2f\u8ba1\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b29\u4f8b|date=7 March 2020|accessdate=7 March 2020|publisher=Gansu Provincial Health Commission}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/84682.html|title=\u7518\u8083\u65b0\u589e4\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b \u7d2f\u8ba1\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b33\u4f8b|date=8 March 2020|accessdate=8 March 2020|publisher=Gansu Provincial Health Commission}}{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/84732.html|title=\u7518\u8083\u65b0\u589e1\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b \u7d2f\u8ba1\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b34\u4f8b|date=10 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020|publisher=Gansu Provincial Health Commission}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/84754.html|title=\u7518\u8083\u65b0\u589e2\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b \u7d2f\u8ba1\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b36\u4f8b|date=11 March 2020|accessdate=12 March 2020|publisher=Gansu Provincial Health Commission}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://wsjk.gansu.gov.cn/single/10910/84805.html|title=\u7518\u8083\u65b0\u589e3\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b \u7d2f\u8ba1\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u786e\u8bca\u75c5\u4f8b41\u4f8b \u7518\u8083\u672c\u5730\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u4f4f\u9662\u75c5\u4f8b\u548c\u5bc6\u63a5\u4eba\u5458\u5b9e\u73b0\u53cc\u6e05\u96f6|date=14 March 2020|accessdate=14 March 2020|publisher=Gansu Provincial Health Commission}}</ref>\n\n==Other international reactions==\nOne [[Dubai]]-based newspaper wrongly claimed in a front-page headline that all cases of the new coronavirus in the region came from the Islamic Republic. That would be convenient for the United Arab Emirates, a federation of seven sheikhdoms home to Dubai whose 13 coronavirus cases predominantly trace back to China.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/40a57a17ae66afbc7ce99494fd71a618|title=Virus response in Mideast tainted by political views of Iran|date=27 February 2020|website=AP NEWS|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302144926/https://apnews.com/40a57a17ae66afbc7ce99494fd71a618|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBrian Hook, the US State Department's envoy on Iran, said that the Iranian government lied \"and their media was instructed not to report on the coronavirus outbreak as it rapidly spread from the religious city of Qom to other cities\".<ref name=\"newyorker1\"/> The US Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]] made a number of accusation against Khamenei in March, saying that Khamanei had lied about the outbreak in Iran and continued to keep [[Mahan Air]] flying to and from China in February, spreading the virus and putting lives at risk, as well as jailing those who spoke out, and that funds for coronavirus had been stolen by officials.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.state.gov/khameneis-lies-about-the-wuhan-virus-put-lives-at-risk/ |title=Khamenei's Lies About the Wuhan Virus Put Lives at Risk|first=Michael R. |last=Pompeo|date=23 March 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/pompeo-tells-khamenei-speaking-the-truth-to-iranians-best-biological-defense-/30485446.html |title=Pompeo Tells Khamenei Speaking The Truth To Iranians 'Best Biological Defense' |date=13 March 2020|work=Radio Farda}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.ibtimes.sg/iran-officials-stole-1-bln-coronavirus-funds-pompeo-says-pushback-against-khamenei-41615 |title= Iran officials stole $1 bln of coronavirus funds, Pompeo says in pushback against Khamenei|date=24 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nThe resistance units of the exiled opposition [[People's Mujahedin of Iran]] (MEK) accused the Iranian government of covering up the true death toll, and gave considerably higher death count, up to 20 times higher than the official figures.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.upi.com/Top_News/Voices/2020/03/04/Iranian-regime-hides-truth-about-coronavirus/7741583347380/ |title=Iranian Regime Hides Truth about Coronavirus |work=UPI |date=4 March 2020 |access-date=5 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305133659/https://www.upi.com/Top_News/Voices/2020/03/04/Iranian-regime-hides-truth-about-coronavirus/7741583347380/ |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> <ref name=\"france24\">{{cite news |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200301-what-is-the-real-size-of-the-coronavirus-epidemic-in-iran |title=What is the real size of the coronavirus epidemic in Iran? |date=1 March 2020 |work=France 24 |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305163602/https://www.france24.com/en/20200301-what-is-the-real-size-of-the-coronavirus-epidemic-in-iran |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> In a joint statement, in late March 2020, one hundred Iranian activists blamed the Supreme Leader, Ali Khamenei, and President Hassan Rouhani for covering up the spread of corona virus and turning it into a catastrophe affecting whole of the country. The signatories include a [[Chemistry]] expert and an adviser to the [[International Atomic Energy Agency]] (IAEA).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/one-hundred-iranian-activists-blame-khamenei-for-severity-of-coronavirus-outbreak/30516266.html|title=One Hundred Activists Blame Khamenei For Severity Of Coronavirus Outbreak In Iran|website=RFE/RL}}</ref>\n\n===Humanitarian assistance===\nThe UN's Children Fund ([[UNICEF]]) has flown aid into Iran. In late February, the first cargo plane with [[Personal Protective Equipment]] (PPE) arrived, another on 3 March and a third aircraft on 16 March. On 3 March, the [[United Arab Emirates]] sent an aircraft with medical supplies and five [[WHO]] experts. [[Uzbekistan]] sent a plane on 16 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ifpnews.com/unicef-uae-uzbekistan-send-aid-to-iran-amid-coronavirus-outbreak|title=UNICEF, UAE, Uzbekistan Send Aid to Iran amid Coronavirus Outbreak|first=IFP Editorial|last=Staff|date=17 March 2020|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320080754/https://ifpnews.com/unicef-uae-uzbekistan-send-aid-to-iran-amid-coronavirus-outbreak|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe fifth batch of testing kits was dispatched to Iran by the [[World Health Organization]] on 28 February.<ref name=\"financial\"/> The group of Chinese medical experts with a new pack of humanitarian aid entered Iran on 29 February.<ref name=\"financial\">{{Cite news|url=https://financialtribune.com/articles/national/102401/more-int-l-medical-aid-arrives-in-iran|title=More Int'l Medical Aid Arrives in Iran|date=29 February 2020|agency=financial tribune|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301004140/https://financialtribune.com/articles/national/102401/more-int-l-medical-aid-arrives-in-iran|archive-date=1 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The [[Ministry of National Defense of the People's Republic of China|Chinese Defense Ministry]] announced on 20 March that test kits, protective suits and medical masks provided by the [[People's Liberation Army]] were handed to the [[Armed Forces of the Islamic Republic of Iran]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.armyrecognition.com/march_2020_news_defense_global_security_army_industry/chinese_army_donates_medical_supplies_to_iranian_army_to_fight_coronavirus.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=23 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321051219/https://www.armyrecognition.com/march_2020_news_defense_global_security_army_industry/chinese_army_donates_medical_supplies_to_iranian_army_to_fight_coronavirus.html |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March 2020, the [[European Union]] pledged \u20ac20m in humanitarian assistance to the Gulf nation. The union said that it was committed to help Iran combat the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] and informed that it would further support its plea for IMF financial help.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-eu-iran/eu-to-provide-20-mln-euros-in-humanitarian-aid-to-iran-idUSL8N2BG6OK|title= EU to provide 20 mln euros in humanitarian aid to Iran|accessdate=23 March 2020|website=Reuters}}</ref>\n\n===US sanctions===\nThe US sanctions have made difficulties for the governmental and non-governmental institutions to provide medication for people who are infected by the Coronavirus. Sending medical supplies to Iran through the recently established Swiss channel requires a written permission from the US. Recently, sanctions on 12 new Iranian entities were imposed by the US Department of State. However, according to the Trump administration, Iran is using sanctions \"as an excuse to hide their own incompetence, including a reluctance to take the necessary tough measures to restrict population movements.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/18/uk-presses-us-to-ease-iran-sanctions-to-help-fight-coronavirus |title=UK presses US to ease Iran sanctions to help fight coronavirus |publisher= the guardian|access-date=18 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nWhile the [[United States sanctions against Iran|US sanctions]] legally allow pharmaceuticals and humanitarian products to be sold to Iran, due to their nature, very few banks are willing to risk sanctions by trading with Iran.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51642926|title=Iran Corona Virus|date=29 February 2020|agency=BBC|access-date=29 February 2020|quote=But Iran says companies find it difficult to process payments with banks unwilling to risk breaking US rules and risk sanctions themselves|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228031515/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51642926|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/03/iran-coronavirus-spreads-sanctions-covid19-iranian-doctors-fear-worst/|title=As Coronavirus Spreads, Iranian Doctors Fear the Worst|date=6 March 2020|agency=ForeignAffairs|access-date=6 March 2020|quote=Should Iranian manufacturers run out of these raw materials, it will be very difficult, if not impossible, to effectively contain and treat COVID-19 in Iran.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304133129/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/03/iran-coronavirus-spreads-sanctions-covid19-iranian-doctors-fear-worst/|archive-date=4 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> This has severely limited the medical supplies available to the Iranian public health system in dealing with the coronavirus outbreak. One right wing lobby group in the United States, [[United Against Nuclear Iran]], has argued to stop all global humanitarian trade with Iran and prevent medical supplies from reaching the country.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://theintercept.com/2020/03/05/iran-coronavirus-medicine-sanctions/|title=Amid Coronavirus Outbreak, Trump-Aligned Pressure Group Pushes to Stop Medicine Sales to Iran|date=6 March 2020|access-date=6 March 2020|quote=UANI\u2019s efforts, however, have extended beyond sanctions into pressuring companies that do legal trade with Iran, often under the Treasury Department\u2019s humanitarian exemptions to sanctions \u2014 including medical-related trades that would presumably aid in combating a massive public health crisis like this coronavirus outbreak.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306000824/https://theintercept.com/2020/03/05/iran-coronavirus-medicine-sanctions/|archive-date=6 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe UK, Pakistan, China, the UN High Commissioner for Human Rights, and experts are pressing the US to ease sanctions on Iran to help it fight the growing coronavirus outbreak.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Wintour|first=Patrick|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/18/uk-presses-us-to-ease-iran-sanctions-to-help-fight-coronavirus|title=UK presses US to ease Iran sanctions to help fight coronavirus|date=18 March 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320191936/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/18/uk-presses-us-to-ease-iran-sanctions-to-help-fight-coronavirus|archive-date=20 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/pakistan-pm-urges-halt-sanctions-coronavirus-hit-iran-200320155952750.html|title=Pakistan PM urges US to halt sanctions on coronavirus-hit Iran|last=Usaid|first=Siddiqui|date=20 March 2020|website=www.aljazeera.com|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321082900/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/pakistan-pm-urges-halt-sanctions-coronavirus-hit-iran-200320155952750.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cepr.net/press-release/us-government-should-immediately-lift-economic-sanctions-to-avoid-causing-more-deaths-from-pandemic-economists-say/|title=US Government Should Immediately Lift Economic Sanctions to Avoid Causing More Deaths From Pandemic, Economists Say|last=|first=|date=18 March 2020|website=Center for Economic and Policy Research|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321082902/https://cepr.net/press-release/us-government-should-immediately-lift-economic-sanctions-to-avoid-causing-more-deaths-from-pandemic-economists-say/|archive-date=21 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=U.S. to Iran: Coronavirus won't save you from sanctions |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-usa-idUSKBN21712L |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=20 March 2020 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321233214/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-usa-idUSKBN21712L |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.rappler.com/world/global-affairs/255747-united-nations-urges-easing-sanctions-iran-others-coronavirus|title=U.N. urges easing of sanctions on Iran, others facing virus|date=24 March 2020|work=[[Rappler]]|access-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live|agency=[[Agence France-Presse]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324182551/https://www.rappler.com/world/global-affairs/255747-united-nations-urges-easing-sanctions-iran-others-coronavirus|archive-date=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://reliefweb.int/report/world/bachelet-calls-easing-sanctions-enable-medical-systems-fight-covid-19-and-limit-global|title=Bachelet calls for easing of sanctions to enable medical systems to fight COVID-19 and limit global contagion|date=24 March 2020|work=[[ReliefWeb]]|access-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live|agency=[[Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324183304/https://reliefweb.int/report/world/bachelet-calls-easing-sanctions-enable-medical-systems-fight-covid-19-and-limit-global|archive-date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Non-government estimates==\n{{POV section|date=March 2020}}\nIn a [[preprint]] paper pending for review on medRxiv journal, Tuite ''et al.'' estimated that as of 25 February, {{circa}} 18,300 infections (95% confidence interval: 3,770\u201353,470; best-case scenario: 380\u20135,320 cases) could have occurred in Iran, based on known exported case counts and air travel links between Iran and other countries, the latter compiled from the data in the past. They concluded that Iran is likely to experience an \"epidemic of significant size\", while lack of identified cases in countries with close travel ties to Iran are because the cases are \"likely being missed, rather than being truly absent\".<ref name=\"Tuite_18k_Iranian_positives\">{{cite news | last1 = Tuite | first1 = Ashleigh R. | last2 = Bogoch | first2 = Isaac | last3 = Sherbo | first3 = Ryan | last4 = Watts | first4 = Alexander | last5 = Fisman | first5 = David N. | last6 = Khan | first6 = Kamran | title = Estimation of COVID-2019 burden and potential for international dissemination of infection from Iran | date = 25 February 2020 | url = https://www.medrxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.02.24.20027375v1 | doi = 10.1101/2020.02.24.20027375 | accessdate = 28 February 2020 | archiveurl = https://archive.today/20200227134801/https://www.medrxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.02.24.20027375v1 | archivedate = 27 February 2020 | url-status = live | journal =  }}</ref>\n\nThe government of Iran had insisted that there was no confirmed COVID-19 in Iran before 19 February 2020, when the first cases were announced.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ir.voanews.com/a/iran-corona/5296552.html|title=\u0645\u0631\u06af \u0628\u0631 \u0627\u062b\u0631 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646\u061b \u067e\u0646\u0647\u0627\u0646\u200c\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06cc \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0645\u0627\u062a\u060c \u0628\u06cc\u200c\u0627\u0639\u062a\u0645\u0627\u062f\u06cc \u0645\u0631\u062f\u0645 \u0631\u0627 \u0627\u0641\u0632\u0627\u06cc\u0634 \u062f\u0627\u062f\u0647 \u0627\u0633\u062a|website=\u0635\u062f\u0627\u06cc \u0622\u0645\u0631\u06cc\u06a9\u0627|language=fa|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221135557/https://ir.voanews.com/a/iran-corona/5296552.html|archive-date=21 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/fa-ir/\u062f\u0648-\u0628\u06cc\u0645\u0627\u0631-\u0645\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627-\u0628\u0647-\u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627-\u062f\u0631-\u0642\u0645-\u062f\u0631\u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a\u0646\u062f/a-52435042|title=\u062f\u0648 \u0628\u06cc\u0645\u0627\u0631 \u0645\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0642\u0645 \u062f\u0631\u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a\u0646\u062f {{!}} DW {{!}} 19 February 2020|website=DW.COM|language=fa-IR|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200220135539/https://www.dw.com/fa-ir/%D8%AF%D9%88-%D8%A8%DB%8C%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D9%85%D8%A8%D8%AA%D9%84%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%88%DB%8C%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D9%82%D9%85-%D8%AF%D8%B1%DA%AF%D8%B0%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%86%D8%AF/a-52435042|archive-date=20 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> However, a letter {{Weasel inline|date=March 2020|text=claimed to be}} from the [[Ministry of Health and Medical Education|Ministry of Health]] to the office of the President that {{Attribution needed|date=March 2020|reason=Who confirmed the authenticity|text=circulated on social media}} suggests that the Iranian authorities were aware of confirmed SARS-CoV-2 cases and deaths {{Weasel inline|date=March 2020|text=many days}} before the official announcement. Government officials said that the letter was a fake.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/persian/iran-51521216|title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u0631\u0633\u0627\u0644 \u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647 \u062f\u0631\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0647 \u0645\u0648\u0627\u0631\u062f \u0627\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627 \u0648 \u0645\u0631\u06af \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u062b\u0631 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0631\u0627 \u062a\u06a9\u0630\u06cc\u0628 \u06a9\u0631\u062f|date=16 February 2020|work=BBC News \u0641\u0627\u0631\u0633\u06cc|access-date=23 February 2020|language=fa}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.radiozamaneh.com/489362|title=\u0645\u0639\u0627\u0648\u0646 \u0648\u0632\u06cc\u0631 \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u0627\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627\u06cc \u06f4\u06f5 \u0646\u0641\u0631 \u0628\u0647 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0631\u0627 \u062a\u06a9\u0630\u06cc\u0628 \u06a9\u0631\u062f|date=16 February 2020|work=[[Radio Zamaneh]]|access-date=26 February 2020|language=fa}}</ref> Another letter also {{Attribution needed|date=March 2020|reason=Who confirmed the authenticity|text=circulated on social media;}} it was signed by interior minister [[Abdolreza Rahmani Fazli]] and sent to Health Minister [[Saeed Namaki]] to request that the announcement of coronavirus outbreak be delayed{{by whom|date=March 2020}} until after the [[2020 Iranian legislative election|parliamentary election]] to avoid a low turnout of voters.{{Dubious|date=March 2020}} The government has also denied this claim.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-health-ministry-denies-letter-warning-related-to-coronavirus-elections/30443145.html|title=\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647 \u0645\u0646\u062a\u0633\u0628 \u0628\u0647 \u0648\u0632\u06cc\u0631 \u06a9\u0634\u0648\u0631 \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u0631\u062a\u0628\u0627\u0637 \u0628\u0627 \u0627\u0646\u062a\u062e\u0627\u0628\u0627\u062a \u0648 \u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062a\u06a9\u0630\u06cc\u0628 \u0634\u062f|website=\u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc\u0648 \u0641\u0631\u062f\u0627|language=fa|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221135004/https://www.radiofarda.com/a/iran-health-ministry-denies-letter-warning-related-to-coronavirus-elections/30443145.html|archive-date=21 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March, [[Graeme Wood (journalist)|Graeme Wood]] stated that he deems the official count \"certainly an undercount\", and provided alternative estimates which he calls \"doomsday figures\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/irans-coronavirus-problem-lot-worse-it-seems/607663/ |first=Graeme |last=Wood |title=Iran Has Far More Coronavirus Cases Than It Is Letting On |work=The Atlantic |date=9 March 2020 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309232036/https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/irans-coronavirus-problem-lot-worse-it-seems/607663/ |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== World Health Organization verification ===\nOn 28 February 2020, [[Michael J Ryan (doctor)|Michael Ryan]], chief of the WHO health emergencies programme told the press that the mortality rate in Iran indicated its outbreak might be more widespread than realised.<ref name=\"BBC\"/>\n\nOn 2 March 2020, The [[World Health Organization]] director general [[Tedros Adhanom]] said in an interview with CNBC that the WHO has its own mechanism for checking national health authorities' statistics and did not see problems with the official Iranian government SARS-CoV-2 and COVID-19 counts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/video/2020/03/02/no-evidence-of-iranian-cover-up-in-virus-crisis-so-far-who.html|title=WHO chief says no evidence of Iranian cover-up in virus crisis so far|date=2 March 2020|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303161026/https://www.cnbc.com/video/2020/03/02/no-evidence-of-iranian-cover-up-in-virus-crisis-so-far-who.html|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March 2020, WHO regional emergency director Rick Brennan said the number of cases reported in Iran could represent only about 20% of the real numbers because testing was restricted to severe cases, as is the case even in some wealthy European countries. He added \"We\u2019ve said the weakest link in their chain is the data. They are rapidly increasing their ability to test and so the numbers will go up... [t]here\u2019s a great commitment and they are taking it seriously from the highest level of government\".<ref name=\"WHO estimate\">{{citation|title=WHO to start coronavirus testing in rebel Syria; Iran raises efforts, official says|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-mideast/who-to-start-coronavirus-testing-in-rebel-syria-iran-raises-efforts-official-says-idUSKBN2133PK|first=Emma|last=Farge|editor-first=Grant|editor-last=McCool|work=Reuters|date=17 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316212446/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-mideast/who-to-start-coronavirus-testing-in-rebel-syria-iran-raises-efforts-official-says-idUSKBN2133PK|archive-date=16 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Other sources ===\n\n==== Members of parliament ====\n[[Masoud Pezeshkian]], the First Deputy of the Parliament of Iran, claimed on 3 March 2020 that the figures reported by Iran's health ministry are \"not real\".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/04/Iran-s-death-toll-due-to-coronavirus-not-real-Iranian-official.html |title=Iran's official figures on coronavirus cases 'not real': Iranian official |date=4 March 2020 |accessdate=5 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304213114/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/04/Iran-s-death-toll-due-to-coronavirus-not-real-Iranian-official.html |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n[[2016 Iranian legislative election|Member of parliament]] for Qom [[Ahmad Amirabadi|Ahmad Amirabadi Farahani]] claimed on 24 February 2020 that COVID-19 had arrived in Qom three weeks prior, in early February, that the first death had occurred on 13 February but was not announced by officials, and that the true number of COVID-19 deaths in Qom was 50.<ref name=\"AJE_Qom_coverup_50deaths\" /><ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-lawmaker-says-fifty-died-of-coronavirus-in-qom-alone-as-crisis-deepens/30451096.html |title=Iran Lawmaker Says Fifty Died Of Coronavirus In Qom Alone, As Crisis Deepens |date=24 February 2020 |work=Radio Farda |access-date=26 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225164803/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-lawmaker-says-fifty-died-of-coronavirus-in-qom-alone-as-crisis-deepens/30451096.html |archive-date=25 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Deputy health minister Iraj Harirchi denied giving false figures, and stated that the death count was 12 with a total of 66 infections.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/24/coronavirus-dead-in-iranian-city-of-qom|title=Coronavirus: Iran denies cover-up after reports of 50 deaths|author1=Sam Jones|author2=Aamna Mohdin|date=24 February 2020|work=The Guardian|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224153012/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/24/coronavirus-dead-in-iranian-city-of-qom|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==== Anonymous sources reported by media ====\nOn 28 February 2020 [[BBC]] reported 210 deaths have occurred in Iran, citing \"sources in the country's health system\", while the official number for the day was 34.<ref name=\"BBC\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51673053|title=Coronavirus kills 210 in Iran \u2013 hospital sources|date=28 February 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=28 February 2020|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229151242/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51673053|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Kianush Jahanpur, the spokesman for the health ministry rejected the BBC report in a tweet.<ref name=\"BBC_210_deaths_Iran\">{{cite news |url = https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-iran-casualties/at-least-210-people-have-died-from-coronavirus-in-iran-bbc-persian-idUSKCN20M2RL | title=Iran rejects BBC Persian report of at least 210 coronavirus deaths | newspaper=[[Thomson Reuters]] | date=28 February 2020 | accessdate=28 February 2020 |archivedate= 28 February 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200228203743/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-iran-casualties/at-least-210-people-have-died-from-coronavirus-in-iran-bbc-persian-idUSKCN20M2RL |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, ''[[The Economist]]'' wrote \"[s]ome in the government think the actual number of cases is closer to 100,000\", while the official count of infected people was about 9,000.<ref name=\"veconomist\" >{{cite news|author= |title= Iran has let its covid-19 outbreak get out of hand|url= https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2020/03/12/iran-has-let-its-covid-19-outbreak-get-out-of-hand|work= [[The Economist]]|date= 12 March 2020|access-date= 13 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312135704/https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2020/03/12/iran-has-let-its-covid-19-outbreak-get-out-of-hand|archive-date= 12 March 2020|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, [[Radio Farda]] reported that \"based on the statements made by local officials in various parts of Iran\", around 2,372 have died, while the official death toll reached 1,556.<ref name=\"Farda 2020\">{{cite web | title='No Lockdown' Says Rouhani As Nearly 14,000 Iranians Contract COVID-19 | website=Radio Farda | date=15 March 2020 | url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/no-lockdown-says-rouhani-as-nearly-14-000-iranians-contract-covid-19/30489072.html | access-date=15 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316131034/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/no-lockdown-says-rouhani-as-nearly-14-000-iranians-contract-covid-19/30489072.html | archive-date=16 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref> Radio Farda also said on 21 March that since Iran's government statistics only include those who had tested positive for the disease, due to a lack of test kits, deaths may be registered as respiratory complications or [[influenza]]. They put their estimate of the number of infections at 16,000 in Tehran alone when the official figure given was 20,610 for the whole country on that date.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/exclusive-more-than-47-000-coronavirus-patients-in-iran-hospitals-2-216-dead/30501369.html |title=Exclusive: More Than 47,000 Coronavirus Patients In Iran Hospitals, 2,216 Dead |date=March 21, 2020|work=Radio Farda}}</ref>\n\n==== Satellite imagery from Qom cemetery ====\n[[Image:3407559 \u062a\u062f\u0641\u06cc\u0646 \u0645\u062a\u0648\u0641\u06cc\u0627\u0646 \u0645\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0622\u0631\u0627\u0645\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0647\u0634\u062a \u0645\u0639\u0635\u0648\u0645\u0647.jpg|thumb|250px|Burial site at Qom's Behesht Masoumeh Cemetery]]\nOn 12 March, ''[[The Washington Post]]'' published satellite images and analysis provided by [[Maxar Technologies]], saying that vast burial pits were being excavated near Qom, said to be used to accommodate the potentially increasing number of victims in the city. The digging of the new section of burial pits began on 21 February, only two days after the government announced their first cases of COVID-19, and then rapidly expanded. The number of fresh graves suggests preparation for a far larger number of deaths.<ref>*{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2020/world/iran-coronavirus-outbreak-graves|title=Coronavirus burial pit so vast they're visible from space|first1=Erin|last1=Cunningham|first2=Dalton|last2=Bennett|date=12 March 2020|work=The Washington Post|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313055935/https://www.washingtonpost.com/graphics/2020/world/iran-coronavirus-outbreak-graves/|archive-date=13 March 2020|url-status=live}}\n*{{YouTube|id=fjuWyXzKBIw|title=Iran is building a massive grave for coronavirus victims}}. published on 13 March 2020 by The Washington Post</ref> Qom municipality official responsible for the city's burial sites said \"the graves had been planned before the outbreak as part of usual procedures in the cemetery\", and some observers pointed that overall length of the purported 100 yards cannot accommodate more than about 75-100 graves.<ref>{{citation|title=Washington Post hypes fake news on coronavirus 'burial pits' in Iran|url=https://www.presstv.com/Detail/2020/03/14/620825/Washington-Post-fake-news-coronavirus-burial-Iran|work=Press TV|date=14 March 2020|access-date=14 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314124434/https://www.presstv.com/Detail/2020/03/14/620825/Washington-Post-fake-news-coronavirus-burial-Iran|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory]]\n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Asia]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{Iran topics}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Iran]]\n[[Category:2020 disasters in Iran]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Iran]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Asia|Iran]]\n", "name_user": "Jerome Charles Potts", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eFebruary 2020:What's a \"cluster\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Iran"}
